(617, 107, 'Single Tent Spot', 'A spot in a shared larger tent or a single tent.', 600.00, 1, 'Sleeping Bag/Mat', 'images/rooms/sonadia_camping_single.jpeg', 'Tents,Campfire,Basic Toilets', '2025-06-07 18:52:54');
INSERT INTO `tourist_spots` (`spot_id`, `name`, `type`, `description`, `country`, `division`, `location`, `image_url`, `historical_significance`, `best_time_to_visit`, `entry_fee`, `opening_hours`, `things_to_do`, `contact_info`, `how_to_go`, `special_tips`, `created_at`) VALUES
(2, 'Cox\'s Bazar Beach', 'Sea', 'Cox’s Bazar is a town on the southeast coast of Bangladesh. It’s known for its very long, sandy beachfront, stretching from Sea Beach in the north to Kolatoli Beach in the south. Aggameda Khyang monastery is home to bronze statues and centuries-old Buddhist manuscripts. South of town, the tropical rainforest of Himchari National Park has waterfalls and many birds. North, sea turtles breed on nearby Sonadia Island.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Cox\'s Bazar Sadar, Cox\'s Bazar', 'images/coxs_bazar.jpg', 'Historically a small port and fishing village, it gained prominence as a tourist spot in the 20th century.', 'November to February for pleasant weather and calm seas. March to May can be hot, while June to October is monsoon season with rough seas.', 'Generally free for public access to the main beach points like Laboni, Sugandha, and Kolatoli.', 'Open 24/7. Lifeguard services are typically available from 9 AM to 6 PM at major points.', 'Swimming (only in designated safe zones), Sunbathing, Beach volleyball & football, Parasailing, Jet skiing, Horse riding, Surfing (beginner-friendly waves), Enjoying spectacular sunsets, Trying fresh seafood from beachside restaurants, Shopping for local handicrafts and Burmese market products.', 'Cox\'s Bazar Tourist Police: +8801769690740 (for safety and assistance)', 'By Air: Direct flights available from Dhaka and other major cities to Cox\'s Bazar Airport (CXB). By Bus: Regular A/C and non-A/C bus services from Dhaka, Chattogram, and other cities. By Car: Well-connected by road networks.', 'Always swim in areas supervised by lifeguards. Be aware of strong currents, especially during monsoon. Bargain while shopping or hiring local transport/activities. Keep the beach clean and dispose of trash responsibly. Sunscreen and hats are recommended during the day. Stay hydrated.', '2025-06-01 17:28:45'),
(3, 'Saint Martin\'s Island', 'Sea', 'Bangladesh\'s only coral island, known for its clear blue waters, coconut groves, and diverse marine life. A popular spot for snorkeling and scuba diving. Saint Martin\'s Island, also known as Narkel Jinjira (Coconut Island), is a small, coral island located in the Bay of Bengal, off the coast of Bangladesh. It\'s a popular tourist destination known for its beaches, crystal-clear waters, and rich marine life. The island is accessible by ferry from Teknaf, a town near Cox\'s Bazar. ', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Teknaf, Cox\'s Bazar', 'images/saint_martin.jpg', 'Named after a British official. Historically used by pirates and later as a settlement.', 'November to February (ships operate, calm sea).', 'Nominal island entry fee collected at jetty; Ferry/ship tickets are separate (BDT 800-2000+ round tr', 'Ferries operate from Teknaf to Saint Martin typically from morning (e.g., 9:30 AM) to afternoon (e.g., 3:00 PM return). Island itself is always accessible for residents/staying tourists.', 'Snorkeling, Scuba diving (limited operators), Beach walking, Cycling around the island, Observing marine life (corals, fish, turtles), Star gazing at night, Trying fresh seafood (especially fish fry), Visiting Chera Dwip (Chhera Island) by boat.', 'Tourist Police Saint Martin: (Contact numbers can be found locally or via Teknaf station)', 'From Dhaka/Chattogram, take a bus to Teknaf. From Teknaf\'s Damdamia Jetty (Jahaj Ghat), take a ferry or ship (Keari Sindbad, Green Line, Bay Cruise etc.) to Saint Martin. Journey takes about 2-3 hours.', 'Protect the coral reefs - do not touch or take corals. Do not litter; carry your trash back. Book accommodation and ship tickets well in advance during peak season (Dec-Jan). Electricity can be limited (generator-based). Mobile network is available but can be weak. Carry enough cash as ATM facilities are very limited or non-existent.', '2025-06-01 17:53:25'),
(4, 'Kuakata Beach', 'Sea', 'Kuakata is a scenic beach town located on the southwestern coast of Bangladesh, known as \"Daughter of the Sea\" or Sagar Kannya. It\'s a 18-kilometer long, 3-kilometer wide sandy beach that offers views of both sunrise and sunset over the Bay of Bengal. Kuakata is a popular tourist destination, a sanctuary for migratory birds, and a pilgrimage site for Hindus and Buddhists. The name \"Kuakata\" is derived from a well dug by early Rakhine settlers on the beach.  ', 'Bangladesh', 'Barisal', 'Kalapara Upazila, Patuakhali District', 'images/kuakata_beach.jpg', 'Historically significant for Rakhine settlers and Buddhist heritage sites like Misripara Buddhist Temple with a large Buddha statue.', 'November to February for pleasant weather. Sunrises and sunsets are visible throughout the year, weather permitting.', 'Generally free to access the beach.', 'Open 24/7. Best to visit for sunrise and sunset.', 'Watching sunrise and sunset from the same point, Beach biking, Visiting nearby attractions like Gangamati Reserved Forest, Fatrar Char (mangrove island), Jhau Bon (pine forest), Misripara Buddhist Temple, Rakhine villages, fishing with local fishermen.', 'Kuakata Tourist Police: (Contact numbers available locally)', 'By Bus: Direct bus services from Dhaka (Gulisthan, Sayedabad) to Kuakata. By Launch: Launch from Dhaka Sadarghat to Patuakhali or Amtali, then local transport (bus/motorcycle) to Kuakata. Road connectivity has improved significantly.', 'Ideal for photography. Respect local Rakhine culture and customs. Check tide times for beach activities. Carry mosquito repellent, especially if visiting nearby forests. Many budget to mid-range hotels available.', '2025-06-01 17:56:21'),
(5, 'Inani Beach', 'Sea', 'Inani Beach, part of the larger Cox\'s Bazar Beach, is a 18-kilometer-long sea beach in Ukhia Upazila, Cox\'s Bazar, Bangladesh. It\'s renowned for its numerous coral stones, which can appear black or green, particularly during the summer and rainy seasons. The beach is known for its peaceful atmosphere, clean waters, and beautiful views of the sea and surrounding hills. ', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Ukhia Upazila, Cox\'s Bazar', 'images/inani_beach.jpg', 'Known for its natural rock and coral formations, making it distinct from other sandy beaches in the area.', 'October to March for calm seas and pleasant weather.', 'Generally free to access.', 'Open 24/7. Daylight hours are best for enjoying the views and activities.', 'Relaxing on the quiet beach, Sunbathing, Photography (especially of the rock formations), Exploring coral stones during low tide, Enjoying the scenic Marine Drive road journey.', NULL, 'Easily accessible by road (CNG, auto-rickshaw, easy bike, car, tourist bus) from Cox\'s Bazar town via the Marine Drive road. Takes about 45-60 minutes.', 'Good for a quieter beach experience. Be careful on the slippery rocks, especially when wet. Carry own snacks and water as facilities are fewer than main Cox\'s Bazar beach. Sunsets are beautiful here.', '2025-06-01 17:58:59'),
(6, 'Patenga Beach', 'Sea', 'Patenga Beach, located 14 kilometers south of Chattogram in Bangladesh, is a popular destination for enjoying the Bay of Bengal\'s beauty. It\'s near the mouth of the Karnaphuli River and known for its vibrant atmosphere and sunset views. While not a pristine, golden sand beach, Patenga offers a unique experience with its concrete walls and large stones used to prevent erosion. ', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Chattogram City', 'images/patenga_beach.jpg', 'An important coastal area for Chattogram Port and features a seawall to protect the coastline.', 'Throughout the year, but evenings and cooler months (October to March) are particularly popular.', 'Generally free. Some specific zones or activities might have fees.', 'Open 24/7. Most activities and food stalls are active in the afternoon and evening.', 'Walking along the seawall, Horse riding, Speedboat rides, Enjoying local snacks (crab fry, fuchka, jhalmuri), Watching sunset over the estuary, Observing ships, Kite flying.', 'Patenga Police Outpost (for assistance)', 'Easily accessible from anywhere in Chattogram city by local transport (bus, CNG, auto-rickshaw, ride-sharing services). Close to Shah Amanat International Airport.', 'Can get very crowded, especially on weekends and holidays. Be mindful of belongings. The beach area has seen recent beautification projects with seating areas. Water quality may not be ideal for swimming due to proximity to the river mouth and port.', '2025-06-01 18:01:03'),
(7, 'Naval Beach', 'Sea', 'Often refers to a section of Patenga Beach near the Bangladesh Naval Academy (BNS Issa Khan), known for its relative cleanliness, orderliness, and scenic beauty. It\'s a more structured part of the coastline.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Patenga, Chattogram City (Near Naval Academy Gate)', 'images/naval_beach.jpg', 'Adjacent to naval installations, hence the name and a more maintained environment.', 'Throughout the year, particularly pleasant in cooler months (October to March). Evenings are popular.', 'Generally free, but access might be controlled or have specific timings for certain areas.', 'Typically accessible during daylight hours and early evening. Respect any posted timings or restricted areas.', 'Walking, Photography, Enjoying the sea breeze and sunset, Relaxing in a more organized environment compared to other parts of Patenga.', NULL, 'Accessible via Patenga road in Chattogram, specifically the area close to the Naval Academy entrance or designated Naval beach point.', 'Maintain cleanliness strictly. Some areas might have restricted access or photography rules due to naval presence. Generally more serene and family-friendly than the main Patenga market area.', '2025-06-01 18:06:46'),
(8, 'Mermaid Beach Area', 'Sea', 'A beautiful and relatively tranquil beach area near Pechar Dwip, south of Cox\'s Bazar main town. Known for the eco-friendly Mermaid Beach Resort and Mermaid Eco Resort, it offers a serene escape with a focus on nature.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Pechar Dwip, Himchari, Cox\'s Bazar', 'images/mermaid_beach.jpg', 'Pioneered eco-tourism concepts in the Cox\'s Bazar region, promoting sustainable practices.', 'October to March for the best weather and calm seas.', 'Public access to the general beach area is typically free. Entry into the private resort areas (Merm', 'Beach is accessible 24/7. Resort facilities have their own timings.', 'Relaxing on the quiet beach, Beachcombing, Photography, Enjoying the natural beauty and artistic installations (at resorts), Kayaking, Surfing (conditions permitting), Dining at the resort restaurants (if accessible).', 'Contact Mermaid Beach Resort or Mermaid Eco Resort for their specific access policies and offerings.', 'Accessible by road from Cox\'s Bazar town (approx. 16-20 km) via the Marine Drive, towards Himchari/Inani. CNGs, auto-rickshaws, or private cars can be hired.', 'Ideal for those seeking tranquility and an eco-friendly, rustic-chic experience. The resorts are known for their unique architecture and ambiance. Public beach areas are less crowded than main Cox\'s Bazar points.', '2025-06-01 18:06:46'),
(9, 'Sonadia Island', 'Sea', 'A pristine and largely uninhabited island west of Cox\'s Bazar, known for its extensive mangrove forests, diverse birdlife (especially migratory birds in winter), red crabs, and as a nesting site for sea turtles.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Maheshkhali Upazila, Cox\'s Bazar', 'images/sonadia_island.jpg', 'An important ecological site and a proposed protected area due to its biodiversity.', 'November to February (for bird watching, pleasant weather, and calmer seas for boat travel).', 'Generally free to visit the island itself. Boat hire charges apply (BDT 2000-5000+ depending on boat', 'Day trips are common. Limited and very basic overnight facilities (homestays or camping with prior arrangement).', 'Bird watching (especially during winter), Exploring mangrove creeks by small boat, Fishing with local fishermen, Camping (requires permission and local guide), Beach walking on pristine and secluded sands, Observing red crabs, Spotting sea turtle tracks (nesting season is typically winter).', 'Local boatmen at Ghat No. 6 or Maheshkhali; Forest Department for permissions if required for certain activities.', 'Accessible by boat (trawler/speedboat) from Ghat No. 6 (Fish Harbour) or Maheshkhali Jetty in Cox\'s Bazar town, or from Maheshkhali island. Journey can take 1-2 hours depending on boat and sea conditions.', 'Eco-sensitive area; strictly avoid littering and disturbing wildlife. Hiring a local guide is highly recommended for navigation and safety. Facilities are very basic; carry your own food, water, first-aid, and other essentials. Permission might be needed for overnight camping from local authorities or Forest Department. Ideal for nature lovers and adventure seekers.', '2025-06-01 18:06:46'),
(10, 'Guliakhali Sea Beach', 'Sea', 'A unique beach in Sitakunda, Chattogram, characterized by green grassy patches (looking like a carpet) extending into the sea, interspersed with water channels, creating a distinctive and picturesque landscape. Also known locally as \"Muradpur Beach\".', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Muradpur Union, Sitakunda Upazila, Chattogram', 'images/guliakhali_beach.jpg', 'A relatively newer tourist spot that has gained popularity for its unique natural formation.', 'October to March (winter and dry season). Avoid peak monsoon (June-August) as the area can become very muddy and difficult to access.', 'Generally free.', 'Daylight hours are recommended for visits. Access depends on tide times to see the grassy plains properly.', 'Walking on the unique grassy fields that meet the sea, Photography of the distinctive landscape, Enjoying the serene environment, Boat rides in the nearby sea or canals, Exploring the surrounding mangrove-like vegetation.', NULL, 'From Dhaka/Chattogram, take a bus to Sitakunda Bazar. From Sitakunda Bazar, hire a CNG or auto-rickshaw to Guliakhali village/beach area (approx. 5-7 km). The last part might require walking.', 'The terrain can be very muddy, especially after rain or during high tide. Wear appropriate water-resistant footwear. Best visited during low tide to fully experience the grassy plains. Limited food/drink options are available locally; it\'s advisable to carry your own. Be mindful of the tide schedule as water levels can change rapidly.', '2025-06-01 18:06:46'),
(11, 'Laboni Beach Point', 'Sea', 'One of the most popular, oldest, and easily accessible points of Cox\'s Bazar beach. Known for its bustling atmosphere, numerous beachside shops, variety of activities, and proximity to many hotels.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Cox\'s Bazar Sadar, Cox\'s Bazar', 'images/laboni_beach.jpg', 'A central hub for tourists in Cox\'s Bazar for decades, marking the main tourist development area.', 'October to March for the best weather and tourist season.', 'Generally free to access the beach.', 'Open 24/7. Most activities, shops, and lifeguard services are active from morning till late evening.', 'Swimming (in designated safe zones), Beach sports (volleyball, football), Horse riding, Parasailing and Jet Skiing (operators nearby), Shopping for local souvenirs, pearls, and Burmese products, Enjoying street food, fresh coconut water, and seafood snacks.', 'Cox\'s Bazar Tourist Information Center; Tourist Police booths are usually present.', 'Centrally located in Cox\'s Bazar town, easily accessible by walking or rickshaw/auto-rickshaw from most hotels in the main tourist zone.', 'Can be very crowded, especially during peak season, weekends, and holidays. Keep belongings secure. Bargain respectfully when shopping or hiring services. Lifeguards are present, but always be cautious while swimming.', '2025-06-01 18:06:46'),
(12, 'Parki Beach', 'Sea', 'A serene and relatively less crowded beach located in Anwara Upazila, south of Chattogram city. It features a long stretch of sandy beach lined with Jhau Bon (pine forest) and offers views of ships at the outer anchorage of Karnaphuli channel.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Anwara Upazila, Chattogram', 'images/parki_beach.jpg', 'A developing tourist spot, gaining popularity as a day-trip destination from Chattogram.', 'October to March for pleasant weather. Evenings are particularly nice.', 'Generally free. Small parking fees for vehicles might apply.', 'Accessible throughout the day. Daylight hours are recommended for safety and enjoyment.', 'Relaxing on the quiet beach, Walking through the Jhau Bon (pine forest), Photography, Picnicking, Enjoying local fish fry from small stalls, Watching the sunset.', NULL, 'Accessible by road from Chattogram city (approx. 1-1.5 hours drive). One needs to cross the Karnaphuli River (via Shah Amanat Bridge or ferry services) and then head towards Anwara Upazila. Local transport like CNGs can be hired.', 'Less crowded than Patenga, making it good for a peaceful outing. Facilities (food stalls, restrooms) might be limited compared to more developed beaches, so carry essentials if planning a longer stay. The road condition to Parki Beach can vary.', '2025-06-01 18:06:46'),
(13, 'Shugondha Beach Point', 'Sea', 'Another popular and bustling access point to Cox\'s Bazar beach, located south of Laboni Point and north of Kolatoli. Known for its wide sandy area, numerous hotels, restaurants, and proximity to Burmese markets.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Cox\'s Bazar Sadar, Cox\'s Bazar', 'images/shugondha_beach.jpg', 'A key tourist area in Cox\'s Bazar that developed rapidly with the growth of tourism, forming part of the main hotel-motel zone.', 'October to March, during the peak tourist season.', 'Generally free to access the beach.', 'Open 24/7. Beach activities, shops, and restaurants are active from morning till late evening.', 'Beach activities like swimming and sunbathing, Parasailing and jet ski rides, Trying out various local and international cuisines at nearby restaurants, Shopping at the numerous Burmese markets and local handicraft stores.', 'Tourist Police booths are usually present in the area.', 'Located in the main hotel-motel zone of Cox\'s Bazar, easily accessible by walking or local transport from most accommodations.', 'Popular and can be quite busy, especially in the evenings. Offers a good range of amenities and dining options. As with other beach points, be cautious with valuables and swim in safe areas.', '2025-06-01 18:06:46'),
(14, 'Nilgiri Mountains', 'Mountain', 'A popular hill resort in Bandarban, about 50 km from Bandarban town, offering breathtaking panoramic views of surrounding hills, clouds, and sometimes the Sangu River. It\'s known for its stunning natural beauty, including the vibrant culture of the Mro tribal villages nearby. Nilgiri is also called the \"Darjeeling of Bengal\" due to its green hills and cloud-filled landscape.  Managed by the Bangladesh Army.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Thanchi Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/nilgiri_mountains.jpg', 'Developed as a tourist spot by the army, it has become one of Bandarban\'s prime attractions.', 'October to March (for clear skies and pleasant weather). Monsoon (June-September) offers lush greenery and clouds, but travel can be challenging.', 'Entry fee applicable (around BDT 50-100 per person, vehicle entry fee separate). Resort booking sepa', 'Typically open from morning till evening for day visitors. Resort guests have 24-hour access to their cottages.', 'Enjoying panoramic views, Photography, Experiencing clouds below (especially in morning/monsoon), Staying at army-run cottages (booking well in advance required), Trying local tribal food at nearby stalls.', 'Nilgiri Resort Booking (via army channels or authorized agents). Local guides in Bandarban.', 'From Bandarban town, hire a Chander Gari (local jeep) or private vehicle. The road is hilly and scenic. Takes about 2-3 hours.', 'Book accommodation well in advance, especially during peak season. Carry warm clothes during winter. Mobile network can be erratic. Respect the local culture and army regulations. The place is very popular, so expect crowds during holidays.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(15, 'Chimbuk Hill', 'Mountain', 'One of the highest and most famous hills in Bandarban, located about 26 km from Bandarban town. Offers stunning views of the surrounding landscape, often described as a \"sea of clouds\".', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Bandarban Sadar Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/chimbuk_hill.jpg', 'A traditional tourist spot in Bandarban, popular for decades.', 'October to March for clear views. Monsoon season for clouds and greenery.', 'Small entry fee may apply at the viewpoint (around BDT 20-50).', 'Daylight hours (e.g., 8 AM to 5 PM).', 'Enjoying scenic views, Photography, Visiting nearby tribal villages (Mro villages are common), Trying local fruits and handicrafts.', 'Local guides in Bandarban. Tourist facilities at Chimbuk are managed by local authorities/army.', 'From Bandarban town, hire a Chander Gari (local jeep), bus, or private vehicle. It\'s on the way to Thanchi/Nilgiri.', 'The viewpoint can get crowded. Combine a trip to Chimbuk with Nilgiri or Shoilo Propat waterfall. Road conditions can be affected during heavy monsoon. Carry water and snacks.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(16, 'Himchari National Park', 'Mountain', 'Located about 12 km south of Cox\'s Bazar, Himchari is known for its tropical rainforest, hills, waterfalls (especially active during monsoon), and diverse flora and fauna. Offers trekking trails and viewpoints.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Ramu Upazila, Cox\'s Bazar', 'images/himchori_park.jpg', 'Established as a national park to conserve the unique biodiversity of the region.', 'November to February for pleasant trekking. Monsoon (June-September) for waterfalls in full flow, but trails can be slippery.', 'Entry fee applicable (around BDT 20-50).', 'Typically open from 9 AM to 5 PM.', 'Trekking, Hiking to waterfalls (Himchari Waterfall, Inani Waterfall nearby), Bird watching, Enjoying views from hilltops, Photography, Exploring the forest ecosystem.', 'Himchari National Park Office (local forest department). Local guides available at the entrance.', 'From Cox\'s Bazar town, hire an auto-rickshaw, CNG, or easy bike. It\'s on the Marine Drive road towards Inani.', 'Wear comfortable trekking shoes. Carry water and insect repellent. Trails can be slippery during/after rain. The main waterfall might be crowded. Be respectful of the forest environment.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(17, 'Tajindong (Vijoy)', 'Mountain', 'One of the highest peaks in Bangladesh (often cited as 2nd or 3rd highest, approx. 986m or 3235 ft). Known locally as \"Vijoy\". Offers challenging trekking and stunning views from the summit.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Ruma Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/tajindong.jpg', 'A significant peak for trekkers and adventure enthusiasts in Bangladesh. Sacred to local communities.', 'November to February (dry season, clearer trails). Avoid monsoon for trekking.', 'No direct entry fee for the peak, but costs include guide fees, transport, and potentially permissio', 'Trekking is done during daylight hours. Overnight stays usually in local villages or basic shelters.', 'Trekking, Hiking, Camping (with guide), Experiencing indigenous culture in nearby villages (e.g., Boga Lake, Passing Para), Photography, Enjoying panoramic views.', 'Local guides in Ruma Bazar. Army/BGB permission often required for trekking in this region.', 'From Bandarban town, go to Ruma Bazar by Chander Gari/bus. From Ruma Bazar, hire a guide and Chander Gari towards Boga Lake. Trek starts from Boga Lake or further points. Requires 2-3 days for the entire trip.', 'High level of physical fitness required. Hiring a registered local guide is mandatory. Obtain necessary permissions. Carry all essentials: good trekking shoes, water, food, first-aid, sleeping bag (if camping), power bank, torchlight. Respect local customs and environment. Travel in a group.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(18, 'Saka Haphong (Mowdok Mual)', 'Mountain', 'Considered by many to be the highest peak in Bangladesh (approx. 1052m or 3451 ft), located on the border with Myanmar. Offers an extremely challenging and remote trekking experience.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Thanchi Upazila, Bandarban (Border area)', 'images/saka_haphong.jpg', 'One of the most challenging and rewarding treks in Bangladesh, attracting hardcore adventurers.', 'November to February (dry season is crucial for this trek).', 'No entry fee for the peak. Significant costs for guides, porters, permits, and logistics.', 'Multi-day trek, done during daylight. Requires careful planning.', 'Extreme trekking, Expedition-style hiking, Camping, Experiencing remote indigenous cultures, Photography of pristine wilderness.', 'Experienced local guides from Thanchi/Remakri. BGB/Army permissions are mandatory and can be complex to obtain.', 'From Bandarban, go to Thanchi Bazar. From Thanchi, boat to Remakri. Trek starts from Remakri towards Doliyan Para, Nafakhum, Jinna Para, Thaikshang Para, then to the summit. Requires 4-7 days.', 'Highest level of physical fitness and trekking experience needed. Mandatory to go with highly experienced registered local guides and porters. Obtain all necessary permits from BGB, Army, and local administration well in advance. This is a very remote and sensitive border area. Carry full camping gear, sufficient food, water purification, extensive first-aid, GPS/map. Travel in a well-prepared group. Respect all local and border regulations.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(19, 'Zow Tlang (Zo Tlang/Misor Daul)', 'Mountain', 'A significant peak in the Bandarban hill tracts, known for its challenging trek and remote beauty. Part of the Politai range.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Ruma/Thanchi Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/zow_tlang.jpg', 'Explored by trekking communities, offers pristine natural views.', 'November to February.', 'Guide fees, transport, and permissions.', 'Multi-day trek.', 'Trekking, Camping, Photography, Experiencing remote nature.', 'Local guides from Ruma or Thanchi.', 'Route typically involves Ruma or Thanchi, then extensive trekking through remote areas. Requires guide.', 'High fitness, experienced guide, permissions, full trekking gear, respect local culture.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(20, 'Maithaijama Haphong', 'Mountain', 'A lesser-known but beautiful peak in the Bandarban region, offering adventurous trekking routes through dense forests and tribal villages.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Belaichari Upazila, Rangamati (or Ruma, Bandarban - location can be debated)', 'images/maithaija_haphong..jpg', 'Offers a glimpse into untouched nature and remote tribal life.', 'November to February.', 'Guide fees, transport, and permissions.', 'Multi-day trek.', 'Trekking, Exploring remote villages, Nature photography, Camping.', 'Local guides from relevant Upazilas.', 'Access is typically through Ruma or Belaichari, followed by boat journeys and long treks. Requires experienced guide.', 'Requires good physical condition, experienced local guide, necessary permissions, and full trekking/camping equipment. Respect local customs.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(21, 'Sippi Arsuang', 'Mountain', 'A notable peak in the Bandarban hill range, offering challenging trails and rewarding views for seasoned trekkers.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Rowangchhari Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/sippi_arsuang.jpg', 'Known among trekking communities for its beauty and difficulty.', 'November to February.', 'Guide fees, transport, and permissions.', 'Multi-day trek.', 'Hardcore trekking, Summit attempt, Camping, Photography.', 'Local guides from Rowangchhari or Bandarban.', 'Route involves reaching Rowangchhari and then trekking with a guide through hilly terrain. Permissions needed.', 'For experienced trekkers only. Excellent fitness, guide, permits, and proper gear are essential.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(22, 'Reng Tlang (Rengmitlang)', 'Mountain', 'A mountain range in Rangamati district, part of the Chittagong Hill Tracts, known for its biodiversity and scenic beauty. Offers opportunities for exploring remote areas.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Belaichhari/Jurachhari Upazila, Rangamati', 'images/reng_tlang.jpg', 'Area is home to diverse ethnic communities and rich flora/fauna.', 'November to March.', 'Guide fees, boat hire, and potentially permissions.', 'Exploration takes multiple days.', 'Trekking, Exploring waterfalls and streams, Visiting remote villages, Bird watching, Nature study.', 'Local guides from Rangamati or relevant Upazilas. Contact local administration for access info.', 'Access usually involves boat journey on Kaptai Lake to remote areas, then trekking. Requires guide and planning.', 'Remote area, ensure safety and carry all essentials. Respect local cultures. Permissions might be needed for certain parts of the range.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(23, 'Jogi Haphong', 'Mountain', 'One of the higher peaks in Bangladesh, located in Bandarban. Known for its challenging ascent and panoramic views. Its height is debated but often cited over 3000 ft.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Thanchi Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/jogi_haphong.jpg', 'A target for serious trekkers in Bangladesh.', 'November to February.', 'Guide fees, transport, and permissions.', 'Multi-day trek.', 'Challenging trekking, Summit attempt, Camping, Photography.', 'Local guides from Thanchi. BGB/Army permissions required.', 'Route from Thanchi, involving boat trips and several days of trekking through remote hilly terrain. Requires a guide.', 'Excellent physical condition, experienced guide, all necessary permits, and full trekking/camping gear are mandatory. Very remote.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(24, 'Dumlong', 'Mountain', 'A significant peak in Rangamati district, often considered one of the highest in that region. Offers challenging treks through remote landscapes.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Belaichhari Upazila, Rangamati', 'images/dumlong.jpg', 'Known for its rugged terrain and pristine natural environment.', 'November to February.', 'Guide fees, boat hire, and permissions.', 'Multi-day trek.', 'Trekking, Exploring remote areas, Camping, Photography.', 'Local guides from Belaichhari or Rangamati. Permissions from local administration/security forces needed.', 'Access via boat on Kaptai Lake to a suitable starting point, then extensive trekking. Mandatory guide.', 'For experienced and fit trekkers. Full preparedness with gear, food, water, first-aid is crucial. Respect local communities and environment.', '2025-06-01 18:33:36'),
(25, 'Kaptai Lake', 'River', 'The largest man-made lake in Bangladesh, created for a hydroelectric project. Known for its scenic beauty, boat rides, and surrounding hills.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Kaptai Upazila, Rangamati', 'images/kaptai_lake.jpg', 'Created in the 1960s by damming the Karnaphuli River, significantly impacting the local Chakma population.', 'September to March (pleasant weather for boating and sightseeing).', 'No direct entry fee for the lake. Boat hire and entry to specific spots (e.g., Shuvolong Waterfall, ', 'Lake is accessible 24/7. Boat services and tourist spots operate during daylight hours (e.g., 9 AM to 5 PM).', 'Boating, Kayaking, Visiting Shuvolong Waterfall, Exploring tribal villages, Hanging Bridge of Rangamati, Peda Ting Ting restaurant, Fishing (with permission).', 'Rangamati Parjatan Complex, Local boatmen associations.', 'From Chattogram, take a bus to Rangamati town. From Rangamati, hire a boat from the Parjatan Ghat or Reserve Bazar Ghat to explore the lake.', 'Hire boats for a full day or half day. Negotiate prices beforehand. Life jackets are recommended. Sunscreen and hats are useful. Many resorts and guesthouses are available around the lake.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(26, 'Boga Lake (Bagakain Lake)', 'River', 'A stunning natural sweetwater lake located high in the hills of Bandarban, surrounded by dense forests and tribal villages. Its creation is shrouded in local legends.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Ruma Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/boga_lake.jpg', 'Sacred to the local Bawm and Marma communities. The lake\'s origin is a subject of folklore.', 'October to April (dry season, easier access). Monsoon offers lush views but difficult travel.', 'Small entry fee (around BDT 20-50) collected by local community/army. Guide fee separate.', 'Accessible during daylight hours. Overnight stays in local cottages or camping (with permission).', 'Trekking to the lake, Boating (non-motorized), Swimming (caution advised), Camping, Experiencing Bawm tribal culture, Photography, Enjoying the serene environment.', 'Local guides in Ruma Bazar. Army/BGB permission is required to visit Ruma and Boga Lake.', 'From Bandarban town, go to Ruma Bazar by Chander Gari/bus. From Ruma Bazar, hire a guide and Chander Gari to near Boga Lake (road condition dependent). The last part often requires trekking.', 'Moderate level of fitness required for the trek. Hiring a local guide is mandatory. Obtain necessary permissions in Ruma. Basic accommodation available in cottages run by locals. Carry essentials like water, snacks, first-aid, power bank. Respect local culture and environment.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(27, 'Madhabpur Lake', 'River', 'A beautiful artificial lake surrounded by tea gardens in Kamalganj, Moulvibazar. Known for its tranquil environment and the reflection of hills in its clear water.', 'Bangladesh', 'Sylhet', 'Kamalganj Upazila, Moulvibazar', 'images/modhupur_national_park.jpg', 'Created by damming a stream to provide water for tea irrigation, it has become a popular tourist spot.', 'October to March (pleasant weather). Monsoon enhances the greenery of tea gardens.', 'Small entry fee for the tea garden area (around BDT 20-30).', 'Typically open during tea garden visiting hours (e.g., 9 AM to 5 PM).', 'Boating, Walking through tea gardens, Photography, Enjoying the serene atmosphere, Bird watching (especially in winter for migratory birds).', 'Madhabpur Tea Estate authorities.', 'From Sreemangal or Moulvibazar town, hire a CNG, auto-rickshaw, or car to Madhabpur Tea Estate. The lake is within the estate.', 'Combine with a visit to Lawachara National Park and other tea gardens in Sreemangal. Respect the tea garden environment. Photography is generally allowed. Limited food stalls nearby, better to carry snacks.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(28, 'Tanguar Haor', 'River', 'A vast freshwater wetland ecosystem in Sunamganj, a Ramsar site of international importance. Known for its rich biodiversity, migratory birds, and unique haor lifestyle.', 'Bangladesh', 'Sylhet', 'Tahirpur & Dharmapasha Upazilas, Sunamganj', 'images/tangua_haor.jpg', 'One of the most important freshwater wetlands in South Asia, crucial for fisheries and bird conservation.', 'November to February (for migratory birds and dry conditions). Monsoon (June-September) offers a different experience with vast expanses of water, but access to some areas can be difficult.', 'No direct entry fee to the haor. Boat hire is the main cost. Fees for watchtowers or specific sanctu', 'Accessible 24/7 by boat. Best explored during daylight.', 'Boat trips (engine boats, houseboats), Bird watching (especially winter), Experiencing haor lifestyle, Fishing (with locals), Visiting watchtowers for panoramic views, Photography, Enjoying fresh haor fish.', 'Local boatmen in Tahirpur or Sunamganj. NGOs working on conservation. District administration for information.', 'From Sylhet or Sunamganj town, go to Tahirpur. From Tahirpur, hire a boat to explore Tanguar Haor. Overnight stays on houseboats are popular.', 'Hire a boat with a reliable boatman and guide. Carry life jackets. Sun protection is essential. Mosquito repellent needed, especially in evenings. Respect the fragile ecosystem and local communities. During monsoon, the haor transforms into a vast inland sea.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(29, 'Jaflong & Shari River', 'River', 'Jaflong is a hill station and popular tourist spot in Sylhet, known for its stone collection activities from the Piyain River (often mistaken for Shari River locally), tea gardens, and proximity to the Indian border. The Shari River nearby is known for its clear blue water.', 'Bangladesh', 'Sylhet', 'Gowainghat Upazila, Sylhet', 'images/jaflong_shari_river.jpg', 'Historically known for stone crushing industry. The area has significant Khasia tribal presence.', 'October to March (pleasant weather, clearer water). Monsoon brings more water but can disrupt stone collection.', 'Entry fee to Zero Point/Jaflong tourist spot (around BDT 15-30). Boat ride charges are separate.', 'Tourist spot typically open from morning till evening.', 'Boating on Piyain River, Observing stone collection, Visiting Khasia villages (Sangrampunji), Exploring tea gardens, Photography, Visiting Zero Point (border area). Shari River (Lalakhal) nearby offers boat rides in its blue waters.', 'Jaflong Tourist Police. Local boatmen.', 'From Sylhet city, take a bus, CNG, or private car to Jaflong (approx. 2 hours). Lalakhal (for Shari River) is a separate trip, often combined.', 'Bargain for boat rides. Be cautious near the border. Water levels and clarity of Shari River can vary by season. Respect local Khasia culture. Many food stalls and souvenir shops available.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(30, 'Nafa-khum Waterfall', 'River', 'One of the largest and most beautiful waterfalls in Bangladesh by volume of water, located in a remote area of Bandarban on the Sangu River.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Thanchi Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/nafa_khum_waterfall.jpg', 'A significant natural attraction for adventure tourists, part of the Sangu River system important to local communities.', 'October to February (dry season, safer for travel and trekking). Avoid peak monsoon due to strong currents and difficult access.', 'No direct entry fee. Costs involve boat hire, guide fees, and permissions.', 'Accessible during daylight hours as part of a multi-day trip.', 'Trekking, Boating on Sangu River, Swimming (with extreme caution and guide\'s advice), Photography, Experiencing remote tribal life (e.g., Remakri).', 'Local guides in Thanchi or Remakri. BGB/Army permission required.', 'From Bandarban town, go to Thanchi Bazar. From Thanchi, hire a guide and take a boat up the Sangu River to Remakri. From Remakri, trek for 2-3 hours to Nafa-khum.', 'Requires good physical fitness. Hiring a local guide is mandatory. Obtain necessary permissions. Carry essentials: water, food, first-aid, appropriate footwear for trekking and river crossings. Life jackets for boat journey. Respect local culture. Travel in a group.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(31, 'Amiakhum Waterfall', 'River', 'A stunning and remote waterfall in Bandarban, known for its pristine beauty and challenging trek. Considered one of the most beautiful waterfalls in Bangladesh.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Thanchi Upazila, Bandarban (near Nakshiyang Roar)', 'images/amiakhum_waterfall.jpg', 'A hidden gem for trekkers, offering a true wilderness experience.', 'November to February (dry season is essential for this trek).', 'No direct entry fee. Significant costs for guides, porters, permits, and logistics.', 'Multi-day trek, done during daylight. Requires careful planning.', 'Extreme trekking, Camping, Swimming (with caution), Photography of untouched nature, Exploring nearby streams and smaller falls like Satbhaikhum.', 'Experienced local guides from Thanchi/Remakri. BGB/Army permissions are mandatory and can be complex.', 'From Bandarban to Thanchi, then boat to Remakri/Padmamukh. Trek starts from there, passing through areas like Nafakhum, Jinna Para, Thuisapara. Requires 3-5 days.', 'Highest level of physical fitness and trekking experience needed. Mandatory to go with highly experienced registered local guides and porters. Obtain all necessary permits. Very remote area. Carry full camping gear, sufficient food, water purification, extensive first-aid, GPS/map. Respect all local and border regulations.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(32, 'Debotakhum (Debota Khum)', 'River', 'A beautiful and serene gorge or \"khum\" (deep water pool surrounded by high cliffs) in Bandarban, accessible by bamboo raft or swimming through narrow passages. Known for its mystical ambiance.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Rowangchhari Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/debotakhum.jpg', 'Considered sacred or mystical by some local communities. \"Debota\" means deity.', 'October to March (dry season, lower water levels make rafting/swimming easier and safer).', 'Guide fee and bamboo raft charges apply. Permission from local authorities/guides.', 'Daylight hours for visits. Usually part of a day trip from Rowangchhari or Kacchaptali.', 'Bamboo rafting through the gorge, Swimming, Photography, Enjoying the tranquility and natural rock formations.', 'Local guides in Rowangchhari or Kacchaptali Bazaar.', 'From Bandarban town, go to Rowangchhari Bazar. From there, hire a guide and take a Chander Gari to Kacchaptali. Trek a short distance to the starting point for Debotakhum. Requires a guide.', 'Life jackets are essential. Non-swimmers should be extremely cautious. The water can be deep. Respect the natural environment. Carry a waterproof bag for electronics. Listen to your guide\'s instructions carefully.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(33, 'Hum Hum Waterfall', 'River', 'A tall and beautiful waterfall located deep within the Rajkandi Reserve Forest in Moulvibazar, Sylhet. Requires a challenging trek through forests and streams.', 'Bangladesh', 'Sylhet', 'Kurma Forest Beat, Rajkandi Reserve Forest, Kamalganj, Moulvibazar', 'images/hum_hum_waterfall.jpg', 'Discovered by tourists relatively recently, it has become a popular destination for adventure seekers.', 'October to February (dry season, easier trek). Monsoon makes the waterfall more voluminous but the trail extremely difficult and slippery.', 'Guide fee is mandatory. Forest department entry fee may apply (around BDT 50-100).', 'Daylight hours for trekking. Start early in the morning.', 'Trekking through dense forest, Crossing streams, Photography, Enjoying the waterfall and natural pool (swimming with caution).', 'Local guides available at Kolabonpara (starting point of trek). Forest Department office in Kamalganj.', 'From Sreemangal/Moulvibazar, go to Kalabagan Para or Kolabonpara via local transport (CNG/Jeep). The trek (2-4 hours each way) starts from there with a mandatory guide.', 'Requires good physical fitness and stamina. Wear appropriate trekking shoes that can get wet. Carry leech repellent, first-aid, water, and snacks. The trail can be very slippery and challenging, especially during/after rain. Listen to your guide. Not recommended for children or those with mobility issues.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(34, 'Baklai Waterfall', 'River', 'Considered one of the tallest waterfalls in Bangladesh (approx. 380 feet), located in a very remote area of Bandarban. Requires a strenuous and multi-day trek.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Thanchi Upazila, Bandarban (near Baklai village)', 'images/baklai_waterfall.jpg', 'A significant challenge for hardcore trekkers in Bangladesh.', 'November to February (dry season is essential for this trek).', 'No direct entry fee. Significant costs for guides, porters, permits, and logistics.', 'Multi-day trek, done during daylight. Requires careful planning.', 'Extreme trekking, Camping, Photography of a very tall waterfall, Experiencing remote village life.', 'Experienced local guides from Thanchi. BGB/Army permissions are mandatory.', 'From Bandarban to Thanchi. Trek starts from Thanchi, often via routes passing through Tindu/Remakri and then towards Baklai Para. Requires several days.', 'Highest level of physical fitness and trekking experience needed. Mandatory to go with highly experienced registered local guides and porters. Obtain all necessary permits. Very remote area. Carry full camping gear, sufficient food, water purification, extensive first-aid. Not for casual tourists.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(35, 'Jadipai Waterfall (Jadipai Jhorna)', 'River', 'A stunning multi-tiered waterfall located near Passing Para in Ruma, Bandarban. Known for its picturesque beauty, especially during the rainy season. Requires trekking.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Ruma Upazila, Bandarban (near Keokradong & Passing Para)', 'images/jadipai_waterfall.jpg', 'One of the most beautiful and popular waterfalls among trekkers in the Keokradong region.', 'September to February (Monsoon for full flow, winter for easier trek).', 'Guide fee is part of the Keokradong/Passing Para trek. No separate entry fee for the waterfall itsel', 'Accessible during daylight hours as part of a trek.', 'Trekking, Photography, Enjoying the waterfall\'s beauty, Bathing in the pool (with caution).', 'Local guides in Ruma Bazar or Boga Lake.', 'From Bandarban town to Ruma Bazar. Then Chander Gari to Boga Lake. Trek from Boga Lake to Keokradong peak, then further trek down to Jadipai via Passing Para. Usually part of a 2-3 day Keokradong trek.', 'Moderate to good physical fitness required. The trail to Jadipai from Passing Para can be steep and slippery, especially during monsoon. Wear good trekking shoes. Hiring a guide is mandatory. Carry water and snacks.', '2025-06-01 18:42:30'),
(36, 'Sundarbans Mangrove Forest', 'Forest', 'The largest single block of tidal halophytic mangrove forest in the world, a UNESCO World Heritage Site. Famous for the Royal Bengal Tiger, spotted deer, crocodiles, and diverse birdlife.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Khulna, Bagerhat, and Satkhira Districts', 'images/sundarbans.jpg', 'A unique ecosystem of global importance, providing critical habitat and coastal protection. Historically significant for its resources and local communities like the Mawalis (honey collectors).', 'November to February (cool and dry weather, best for wildlife sighting). Avoid peak monsoon for boat tours.', 'Permits required from Forest Department (fees vary for zones like Karamjal, Kotka, Kochikhali, Hiron', 'Forest entry and boat tours are typically during daylight hours. Overnight stays on specialized tour boats or at limited Forest Department guesthouses (advance booking essential).', 'Boat safaris (canal cruising), Wildlife spotting (tigers are elusive, deer, monkeys, crocodiles, birds are common), Jungle trekking (with armed guards in certain zones), Visiting wildlife sanctuaries (e.g., Kotka, Kochikhali), Experiencing local culture (e.g., fishing villages), Photography.', 'Khulna Forest Circle Office, Mongla Forest Office. Numerous private tour operators in Khulna and Mongla.', 'From Dhaka/Khulna, travel to Mongla Port (most common entry point) or Satkhira (for western parts). From Mongla, hire a tour boat/package for multi-day trips into the Sundarbans. Day trips to Karamjal are also possible from Mongla.', 'Travel with a registered and experienced tour operator and guide. Follow all Forest Department rules strictly. Do not disturb wildlife or vegetation. Carry mosquito repellent, sunscreen, hats, binoculars, and appropriate clothing. Life jackets are essential on boats. Be prepared for basic facilities on most tour boats. Tiger sightings are rare and require luck and patience.', '2025-06-01 18:54:33'),
(37, 'Lama Hill Forest Area', 'Forest', 'Lama is an upazila in Bandarban known for its picturesque hills, dense forests, rubber plantations, and small tribal communities. It offers opportunities for light trekking and experiencing serene nature.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Lama Upazila, Bandarban', 'images/lama_hill_forest.jpeg', 'Part of the Chittagong Hill Tracts, with a rich history of indigenous communities and natural resource management.', 'October to March (pleasant weather for exploring). Monsoon brings lush greenery but can make trails slippery.', 'Generally no specific entry fee for general forest areas. Fees may apply for specific eco-parks or p', 'Accessible during daylight hours.', 'Light trekking, Visiting rubber plantations, Exploring small streams and waterfalls (seasonal), Photography, Interacting with local communities (with respect and permission), Enjoying panoramic views from hilltops.', 'Local Upazila administration or local guides for specific trails.', 'From Bandarban town or Chakaria (Cox\'s Bazar district), take a bus or Chander Gari to Lama Bazar. From Lama, explore surrounding areas with local guidance.', 'Engage a local guide for trekking or visiting villages. Respect local customs and traditions. Roads can be challenging, especially during monsoon. Basic accommodation available in Lama town.', '2025-06-01 18:54:33');
INSERT INTO `tourist_spots` (`spot_id`, `name`, `type`, `description`, `country`, `division`, `location`, `image_url`, `historical_significance`, `best_time_to_visit`, `entry_fee`, `opening_hours`, `things_to_do`, `contact_info`, `how_to_go`, `special_tips`, `created_at`) VALUES
(38, 'Fatikchhari Forest & Tea Gardens', 'Forest', 'Fatikchhari Upazila in Chattogram is known for its extensive forest areas, rolling hills, and numerous tea gardens, offering scenic landscapes and opportunities for nature walks.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Fatikchhari Upazila, Chattogram', 'images/F.jpg', 'Historically an area of tea cultivation and forestry.', 'October to March (pleasant weather for walking and tea garden visits).', 'No general entry fee for forest areas. Entry to specific tea estates might require permission or hav', 'Daylight hours for exploration.', 'Walking through forest trails (with local guidance), Visiting tea gardens (some allow visitors to see processing), Photography, Enjoying the greenery and hilly terrain, Bird watching.', 'Local Upazila Parishad, Fatikchhari. Contact specific tea estates for visit permissions.', 'From Chattogram city, take a bus or CNG/private car towards Fatikchhari. Specific areas like Udalia Tea Garden or Hazarikhil Wildlife Sanctuary (nearby) can be targeted.', 'Best to go with someone familiar with the area. Respect private property, especially within tea estates. Roads to interior areas can be unpaved. Carry water and snacks.', '2025-06-01 18:54:33'),
(39, 'Char Kukri Mukri Wildlife Sanctuary', 'Forest', 'A char (island) area in Bhola district, known for its mangrove forests (though different from Sundarbans), deer population, migratory birds, and fishing communities. It\'s a designated wildlife sanctuary.', 'Bangladesh', 'Barisal', 'Char Fasson Upazila, Bhola', 'images/char_kukri_mukri.jpg', 'An important coastal char ecosystem, vital for wildlife and local livelihoods.', 'November to February (for bird watching and pleasant weather).', 'Forest Department permit might be required for entry into the sanctuary core area. Boat hire is the ', 'Day trips are common. Limited and basic overnight stay options (e.g., Forest Department rest house, local homes - require prior arrangement).', 'Boat trips through canals, Wildlife spotting (deer, monkeys, birds), Bird watching (especially winter migrants), Exploring mangrove forests, Experiencing the char lifestyle, Fishing.', 'Bhola District Forest Office, Char Fasson Upazila Nirbahi Officer.', 'From Dhaka/Barisal, take a launch to Bhola (Betua or Char Fasson). From Char Fasson, hire a trawler or speedboat to Char Kukri Mukri. This can take several hours.', 'Remote location with basic facilities. Travel in a group with a local guide. Carry all essentials: food, water, first-aid, insect repellent, power bank. Respect the fragile environment and local culture. Ideal for nature enthusiasts and those seeking offbeat experiences.', '2025-06-01 18:54:33'),
(40, 'Ratargul Swamp Forest', 'Forest', 'One of the few freshwater swamp forests in Bangladesh, located in Gowainghat, Sylhet. During monsoon, the entire forest goes under 20-30 feet of water. Known for its unique ecosystem and boat rides through submerged trees.', 'Bangladesh', 'Sylhet', 'Gowainghat Upazila, Sylhet', 'images/ratargul_swamp_forest.jpg', 'A unique freshwater swamp ecosystem, home to diverse aquatic and terrestrial flora and fauna.', 'Monsoon (June to September) is the best time to see the forest submerged and enjoy boat rides. Winter (November to February) offers a different view with less water, allowing some walking trails.', 'Entry fee (around BDT 50-100 per person) collected by Forest Dept/local authorities. Boat hire is se', 'Typically open from morning till evening. Boating is best during daylight.', 'Boat ride through the submerged forest (monsoon), Kayaking, Walking on trails (winter), Bird watching, Photography, Enjoying the serene and unique forest environment.', 'Forest Department office at Ratargul or Gowainghat. Local boatmen at the ghat.', 'From Sylhet city, go to Gowainghat. From Gowainghat, hire a CNG/auto-rickshaw to the Ratargul boat ghat. Then hire a boat to explore the forest.', 'Life jackets are recommended for boat rides. Do not disturb wildlife. Avoid littering. During monsoon, the water can be deep. Listen to boatmen\'s advice. Carry waterproof bags for electronics.', '2025-06-01 18:54:33'),
(41, 'Modhupur National Park', 'Forest', 'One of the oldest national parks in Bangladesh, located in Tangail and Mymensingh districts. Known for its Sal (Shorea robusta) forest, diverse wildlife including monkeys and deer, and picnic spots.', 'Bangladesh', 'Mymensingh', 'Madhupur Upazila, Tangail & Muktagachha Upazila, Mymensingh', 'images/modhupur_national_park.jpg', 'Historically a royal hunting ground, later declared a national park to conserve the Sal forest ecosystem.', 'October to March (pleasant weather for walking and wildlife sighting).', 'Entry fee applicable (around BDT 20-50 per person). Fees for specific attractions like watchtowers o', 'Typically open from 9 AM to 5 PM.', 'Jungle trekking/walking, Wildlife spotting (monkeys, deer, various birds), Visiting watchtowers for views, Picnicking, Cycling, Visiting tribal villages (Garo community) nearby.', 'Modhupur National Park Range Office (Forest Department).', 'From Dhaka or Mymensingh, take a bus towards Tangail/Madhupur. Get down at Rasulpur or Dokhla, then take local transport (rickshaw/CNG) to the park entrance.', 'Engage a local guide for better exploration and safety. Do not feed the animals. Keep the park clean. Some areas might have limited facilities. The forest has faced challenges due to encroachment, so responsible tourism is important.', '2025-06-01 18:54:33'),
(42, 'Mahasthangarh', 'Historical', 'One of the earliest urban archaeological sites in Bangladesh, representing the ancient city of Pundranagara. Ruins date back to at least the 3rd century BCE.', 'Bangladesh', 'Rajshahi', 'Shibganj Upazila, Bogura District', 'images/mahasthangarh.jpg', 'Capital of the Pundra Kingdom, significant during Maurya, Gupta, Pala, and Sena dynasties. Features a fortified citadel, numerous mounds, temples, and a museum.', 'October to March (pleasant weather for exploring ruins).', 'Entry fee for museum and some specific sites (e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals, higher for foreigners).', 'Typically 10:00 AM to 5:00 PM (Museum and site timings may vary, closed on certain days/half-days - check locally).', 'Exploring archaeological ruins (citadel walls, Govinda Bhita, Bairagir Bhita, Mankalir Kundo), Visiting Mahasthangarh Museum, Photography, Learning about ancient history.', 'Mahasthangarh Museum, Department of Archaeology.', 'From Bogura town, take a bus, CNG, or auto-rickshaw to Mahasthangarh (approx. 13 km north).', 'Wear comfortable walking shoes. Carry water and sun protection. Hire a local guide for detailed historical insights. The site is extensive, so plan for several hours.', '2025-06-01 19:03:02'),
(43, 'Sompura Mahavihara (Paharpur Buddhist Vihara)', 'Historical', 'A UNESCO World Heritage Site, it is among the best known Buddhist viharas in the Indian Subcontinent and is one of the most important archaeological sites in the country. It was a renowned intellectual centre from the 8th to 12th centuries.', 'Bangladesh', 'Rajshahi', 'Badalgachhi Upazila, Naogaon District', 'images/sompura_mahavihara.jpg', 'Built by the Pala king Dharmapala (781–821 AD). It was a significant centre for Mahayana Buddhism. The quadrangular structure with a central stupa and numerous monastic cells is unique.', 'October to March (cooler weather).', 'Entry fee applicable (e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals, higher for foreigners). Museum fee separate.', 'Typically 10:00 AM to 5:00 PM (closed on Sundays and public holidays, half-day on Mondays - verify locally).', 'Exploring the vast monastery complex, Visiting the central stupa, Examining terracotta plaques, Visiting the adjacent museum, Photography.', 'Paharpur Museum, Department of Archaeology.', 'From Naogaon town or Joypurhat town, take a bus or CNG/auto-rickshaw to Paharpur (approx. 32 km from Naogaon, 12 km from Joypurhat).', 'Allow several hours to explore the large site. Wear comfortable shoes. A guide can enhance the experience. The museum houses artifacts found from the site.', '2025-06-01 19:03:02'),
(44, 'Lalbagh Fort (Fort Aurangabad)', 'Historical', 'An incomplete 17th-century Mughal fort complex in Dhaka, started by Prince Muhammad Azam Shah, son of Emperor Aurangzeb. Features a mosque, the tomb of Bibi Pari, and the Diwan-i-Aam.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Lalbagh, Old Dhaka', 'images/lalbagh_fort1.jpg', 'Construction started in 1678 but was halted. Associated with legends, particularly regarding Bibi Pari, daughter of Shaista Khan.', 'October to March (pleasant weather).', 'Entry fee applicable (e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals, higher for foreigners).', 'Summer (Apr-Sep): 10 AM - 6 PM. Winter (Oct-Mar): 9 AM - 5 PM. Friday: Opens after Jumma prayer. Closed on Sundays and public holidays. (Verify timings).', 'Exploring the fort structures (Tomb of Bibi Pari, Lalbagh Fort Mosque, Diwan-i-Aam), Visiting the small museum inside, Photography, Enjoying the gardens.', 'Lalbagh Fort Museum, Department of Archaeology.', 'Located in Old Dhaka, accessible by rickshaw, CNG, auto-rickshaw, or bus from various parts of Dhaka city.', 'Old Dhaka can be congested; plan travel time. Wear comfortable shoes. A guide can explain the history. Be mindful of prayer times if visiting the mosque.', '2025-06-01 19:03:02'),
(45, 'Mainamoti Ruins (Moinamoti)', 'Historical', 'An extensive area of ancient Buddhist archaeological sites, including numerous stupas, monasteries (viharas), and other ruins dating from the 7th to 12th centuries. Key sites include Salban Vihara, Kotila Mura, Charpatra Mura.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Cumilla Sadar Dakshin Upazila, Cumilla District', 'images/mainamoti_ruins.jpg', 'Represents a significant Buddhist civilization under the Deva and Chandra dynasties. Salban Vihara was a large residential monastery.', 'October to March.', 'Entry fee for Salban Vihara and Mainamoti Museum (e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals, higher for foreigners', 'Salban Vihara & Museum: Typically 10 AM - 5 PM (closed Sundays and public holidays, half-day Mondays - verify locally).', 'Exploring Salban Vihara (monastery ruins), Visiting Kotila Mura (three stupas), Charpatra Mura, Ananda Vihara, Visiting the Mainamoti Museum which houses rich collection of artifacts.', 'Mainamoti Museum, Department of Archaeology.', 'From Cumilla town, take a CNG or auto-rickshaw to Mainamoti/Salban Vihara (approx. 8 km).', 'The sites are spread out, so plan for local transport between them if not walking. Wear comfortable shoes. A guide is recommended for understanding the various sites.', '2025-06-01 19:03:02'),
(46, 'Ahsan Manzil (Pink Palace)', 'Historical', 'A former official residential palace and seat of the Nawab of Dhaka. An imposing pink structure on the banks of the Buriganga River, now a museum.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Kumartoli, Old Dhaka (near Sadarghat)', 'images/ahsan_manzil.jpg', 'Built in 1859-1872 by Nawab Abdul Ghani, it witnessed many historical events of the late 19th and early 20th centuries. Renovated and converted into a museum.', 'October to March.', 'Entry fee applicable (e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals, higher for foreigners).', 'Summer (Apr-Sep): 10:30 AM - 5:30 PM. Winter (Oct-Mar): 9:30 AM - 4:30 PM. Friday: 3:00 PM - 7:30 PM. Closed on Thursdays and public holidays. (Verify timings).', 'Exploring the palace rooms and galleries showcasing artifacts, furniture, portraits of Nawabs, Learning about the history of Dhaka and the Nawab family, Photography (exterior usually allowed, interior might have restrictions).', 'Ahsan Manzil Museum authorities.', 'Located in Old Dhaka near Sadarghat launch terminal. Accessible by rickshaw, CNG, or local bus from various parts of Dhaka.', 'Check updated opening hours before visiting. Old Dhaka is crowded; allow travel time. Photography rules might apply for interiors.', '2025-06-01 19:03:02'),
(47, 'Panam Nagar (Panam City)', 'Historical', 'An ancient historical city in Sonargaon, Narayanganj. It was a flourishing trading center for cotton fabrics, especially muslin, during the 17th to 19th centuries. Features rows of well-preserved colonial-era buildings.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Sonargaon Upazila, Narayanganj District', 'images/panam_nagar.jpg', 'Represents the architecture and lifestyle of wealthy Hindu merchants during the British colonial period. Many buildings are now in a dilapidated but atmospheric state.', 'October to March.', 'Entry fee applicable (e.g., BDT 15-100 for locals, higher for foreigners).', 'Typically 9/10 AM to 5 PM. (Verify timings, may close earlier in winter or be closed on certain days).', 'Walking through the old street, Admiring colonial architecture, Photography, Visiting the nearby Sonargaon Folk Art and Craft Museum.', 'Department of Archaeology. Local caretakers.', 'From Dhaka (Gulistan), take a bus to Mograpara Chowrasta in Sonargaon (approx. 1-1.5 hours). From Mograpara, take a rickshaw or auto-rickshaw to Panam Nagar.', 'Wear comfortable shoes for walking. Some buildings are fragile; do not enter unsafe structures. Combine with a visit to Sonargaon Museum and Zainul Abedin Memorial Park.', '2025-06-01 19:03:03'),
(48, 'Durga Sagar Dighi', 'Historical', 'The largest man-made pond (dighi) in southern Bangladesh, located in Barisal. It has a small island in the middle with a shrine. Offers a serene environment.', 'Bangladesh', 'Barisal', 'Babuganj Upazila, Barisal District', 'images/durgasagar_dighi.jpg', 'Excavated in 1780 by Rani Durgabati, wife of Raja Joy Narayan, to alleviate water scarcity for the local people.', 'Throughout the year. Winter (November to February) is pleasant.', 'Small entry fee (around BDT 10-20).', 'Typically open during daylight hours (e.g., 9 AM to 5 PM).', 'Walking around the dighi, Boating (if available), Visiting the island shrine, Picnicking, Enjoying the peaceful atmosphere.', 'Local administration managing the site.', 'From Barisal city, take a bus or auto-rickshaw/CNG towards Babuganj (approx. 11 km).', 'A good spot for a quiet outing. Basic facilities available. Can be combined with other attractions in Barisal.', '2025-06-01 19:03:03'),
(49, 'Tajhat Palace (Tajhat Rajbari)', 'Historical', 'A magnificent historical palace in Rangpur, built by Maharaja Kumar Gopal Lal Roy in the early 20th century. Now serves as the Rangpur Museum.', 'Bangladesh', 'Rangpur', 'Tajhat, Rangpur Sadar Upazila, Rangpur District', 'images/tajhat_palace.webp', 'An example of Indo-Saracenic architecture, it was the residence of the Tajhat zamindars. The museum houses artifacts from the region, including terracotta, manuscripts, and coins.', 'October to March.', 'Entry fee for palace/museum (e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals, higher for foreigners).', 'Museum hours: Typically 10 AM - 5 PM (closed Sundays and public holidays, half-day Mondays - verify locally).', 'Exploring the palace architecture, Visiting the museum galleries, Photography of the exterior and gardens, Learning about local history.', 'Tajhat Palace Museum, Department of Archaeology.', 'From Rangpur city, take a rickshaw or auto-rickshaw to Tajhat (approx. 3 km southeast of the city center).', 'Check museum opening days and hours before visiting. The palace grounds are also pleasant for a walk.', '2025-06-01 19:03:03'),
(50, 'Bhitargarh Fort City', 'Historical', 'The largest fortified city in the Himalayan foothills, located in Panchagarh district, bordering India. It is an extensive archaeological site with ramparts, moats, and ruins dating back to possibly the 6th-12th centuries.', 'Bangladesh', 'Rangpur', 'Amar Khana Union, Panchagarh Sadar Upazila, Panchagarh District', 'images/bhitargarh_fort.webp', 'A significant early medieval period fortified city, covering a large area with complex defense structures. Research and excavation are ongoing.', 'November to February (dry and cool weather).', 'Generally no entry fee for exploring the vast area, but access to specific excavated sites or future', 'Accessible during daylight hours.', 'Exploring the ancient ramparts and moats, Visiting excavated sites (Maharajar Dighi, temples), Photography, Learning about the region\'s early history. It\'s a site for those interested in archaeology and history.', 'Department of Archaeology. Local guides might be available.', 'From Panchagarh town, hire a local transport (auto-rickshaw/CNG) to Bhitargarh area (approx. 15-20 km). The site is spread out.', 'The site is very large and not fully developed for tourism. Wear comfortable shoes. It\'s advisable to go with someone who knows the area or a local guide. Carry water and snacks.', '2025-06-01 19:03:03'),
(51, 'Alexandar Castle (Alexander Castle)', 'Historical', 'A colonial-era structure in Mymensingh town, built by Maharaja Suryakanta Acharya Chowdhury in 1879 as a garden house or guest house. Named after a then District Magistrate, Mr. Alexander.', 'Bangladesh', 'Mymensingh', 'Mymensingh City', 'images/alexandar_castle.jpg', 'An example of colonial architecture, it has served various purposes over the years, including as a teacher\'s training college library. It holds local historical importance.', 'Throughout the year. Visit during daylight hours.', 'May not have a formal entry fee if used for public/educational purposes. Check locally if specific a', 'Depends on its current use (e.g., library hours if still functioning as such).', 'Viewing the colonial architecture, Photography (exterior), Learning about its local history (if information is available on site).', 'Local administration or current occupants (e.g., college authorities).', 'Located within Mymensingh city, accessible by rickshaw or auto-rickshaw.', 'It\'s primarily an architectural landmark. Interior access might be limited depending on its current function. Best to inquire locally about visiting.', '2025-06-01 19:03:03'),
(52, 'Bijoypur Fort (Possible reference to Bijoy Singh Dighi area)', 'Historical', 'If referring to the area around Bijoy Singh Dighi in Feni, it has historical links to Raja Bijoy Singh. The dighi itself is large. Specific \"fort\" ruins might be minimal or refer to ancient earthworks.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Bijoypur, Feni Sadar Upazila, Feni District', 'images/bijoypur_fort_dighi.jpg', 'Associated with the legend of Raja Bijoy Singh. The large dighi (pond) is a prominent feature.', 'Throughout the year. Pleasant in cooler months (October-March).', 'Generally no entry fee for the dighi area.', 'Accessible during daylight hours.', 'Visiting the Bijoy Singh Dighi, Enjoying the serene environment, Learning local legends, Photography.', 'Local Union Parishad or Upazila office.', 'From Feni town, take local transport (CNG/auto-rickshaw) to Bijoypur.', 'This is more of a local historical site centered around a large pond. \"Fort\" might be a traditional name rather than prominent structural ruins. Clarify local understanding of the \"fort\".', '2025-06-01 19:03:03'),
(53, 'Natore Rajbari (Natore Royal Palace / Rani Bhabani Rajbari)', 'Historical', 'A prominent royal palace complex in Natore, residence of the Natore Raj family, most famously Rani Bhabani. The complex includes several structures and large ponds (dighis).', 'Bangladesh', 'Rajshahi', 'Natore Sadar Upazila, Natore District', 'images/natore_rajbari.jpg', 'Seat of the powerful Natore Raj, one of the largest zamindaris in Bengal. Rani Bhabani was a renowned philanthropist and able administrator in the 18th century.', 'October to March.', 'Small entry fee usually applicable (e.g., BDT 10-20).', 'Typically open during daylight hours (e.g., 9 AM to 5 PM).', 'Exploring the palace buildings (Boro Taraf, Chhoto Taraf), Visiting temples within the complex, Walking around the dighis, Photography, Learning about the history of Natore Raj and Rani Bhabani.', 'Natore Rajbari caretaker/local administration.', 'Located in Natore town, easily accessible by rickshaw or auto-rickshaw from the bus stand or railway station.', 'Some parts of the palace may be better preserved than others. A guide can provide historical context. The complex is quite large.', '2025-06-01 19:03:03'),
(54, 'Golden Temple (Bandarban Zila Swarno Mandir)', 'Worship', 'The Buddha Dhatu Jadi temple, one of the Buddhist shrines in Bandarban, attracts a lot of tourists throughout the year. The temple is better known as the Golden Temple. The holy place of Bandarban for the Buddhist people is the Golden Temple. This temple is situated on the top of a high hill in Balaghata area, nine kilometers away from Bandarban city, a green land of natural beauty.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Pulpara, Balaghata, Bandarban Sadar', 'images/golden_temple_bandarban.jpg', 'The largest Theravada Buddhist temple in Bangladesh, built in the Arakanese architectural style. A significant pilgrimage site and tourist attraction.', 'Throughout the year. Mornings and late afternoons are pleasant.', 'Entry fee applicable (around BDT 30-50).', 'Typically open from morning to evening (e.g., 8 AM to 6 PM). May close during lunch breaks or specific prayer times.', 'Admiring the architecture, Viewing Buddhist statues, Enjoying panoramic views, Photography (respectful), Learning about Buddhist culture.', 'Temple authorities.', 'From Bandarban town, hire a CNG or auto-rickshaw (approx. 4 km).', 'Dress modestly (cover shoulders and knees). Remove shoes before entering temple premises. Maintain silence and respect religious customs. Photography might be restricted in certain areas.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(55, 'Anderkilla Shahi Jame Masjid', 'Worship', 'One of the oldest and most historically significant mosques in Chattogram city, built during the Mughal era.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Anderkilla, Chattogram City', 'images/anderkilla_mosque.jpg', 'Built by Mughal Subahdar Shaista Khan in 1667 on a hilltop that was once the site of a Magh fort. \"Anderkilla\" means \"inner fort\".', 'Throughout the year. Visit outside of prayer times for general viewing.', 'No entry fee for prayer or general visit.', 'Open for daily prayers. For general visits, avoid main prayer congregations.', 'Observing Mughal architecture, Offering prayers (for Muslims), Photography (exterior), Learning about its history.', 'Mosque committee.', 'Located in the heart of Chattogram city, easily accessible by local transport.', 'Dress modestly. Maintain silence and respect if visiting during prayer times. Non-Muslims may be allowed to visit outside prayer times but should inquire respectfully.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(56, 'Adinath Temple, Maheshkhali', 'Worship', 'An ancient Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva, located on the summit of Mainak Hill on Maheshkhali Island, near Cox\'s Bazar. Offers scenic views.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Maheshkhali Island, Cox\'s Bazar District', 'images/Adinath Temple, Maheshkhali.webp', 'Believed to be a very old pilgrimage site. The temple attracts many devotees, especially during the annual fair in the month of Falgun (Feb-Mar).', 'October to March (pleasant weather for island visit and temple climb). The annual fair time is also popular.', 'No entry fee for the temple, but donations are welcome. Boat fare to Maheshkhali and local transport', 'Open daily, typically from morning to evening. Specific puja timings apply.', 'Climbing the hill to the temple, Offering prayers, Enjoying panoramic views of the island and sea, Photography, Visiting the nearby Buddhist pagoda and salt fields on Maheshkhali.', 'Temple committee.', 'From Cox\'s Bazar (Ghat No. 6 or near Airport), take a speedboat or trawler to Maheshkhali Island (approx. 30-60 mins). From Maheshkhali ghat, take a rickshaw or auto-rickshaw to the foothill of Adinath Temple.', 'The climb to the temple involves many stairs. Dress modestly. Be respectful of religious customs. The annual fair can be very crowded.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(57, 'Bagha Mosque', 'Historical', 'A historic mosque in Rajshahi, renowned for its exquisite terracotta ornamentation. Built in the 16th century during the Sultanate period.', 'Bangladesh', 'Rajshahi', 'Bagha Upazila, Rajshahi District', 'images/bagha_mosque.jpg', 'Built by Sultan Nusrat Shah in 1523 AD. It is a prime example of Sultanate-era mosque architecture in Bengal, particularly noted for its intricate terracotta work.', 'October to March.', 'Small entry fee may apply (check locally, often managed by Dept. of Archaeology).', 'Typically accessible during daylight hours, outside of prayer times for detailed viewing.', 'Admiring terracotta artwork, Observing Sultanate architecture, Photography, Offering prayers (for Muslims).', 'Department of Archaeology. Local mosque committee.', 'From Rajshahi city, take a bus or CNG towards Bagha Upazila (approx. 40 km southeast).', 'A significant architectural heritage site. Dress modestly. Photography of terracotta details is popular.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(58, 'Shat Gombuj Mosque (Sixty Dome Mosque)', 'Historical', 'A UNESCO World Heritage Site in Bagerhat, it is the largest Sultanate-era mosque in Bangladesh. Despite its name, it has 77 domes plus 4 corner towers (total 81).', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Bagerhat Sadar Upazila, Bagerhat District', 'images/shat_gombuj_mosque.jpg', 'Built by Khan Jahan Ali in the 15th century. A magnificent example of early Islamic architecture in Bengal, characterized by its thick walls and numerous domes.', 'October to March.', 'Entry fee applicable (e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals, higher for foreigners).', 'Typically 9/10 AM to 5 PM (closed on Sundays and public holidays, half-day Mondays - verify locally).', 'Exploring the vast prayer hall, Admiring the architecture, Photography, Visiting nearby historical sites in Bagerhat (e.g., Khan Jahan Ali\'s Tomb, Nine Dome Mosque).', 'Department of Archaeology. Bagerhat Museum.', 'From Khulna or Bagerhat town, take a bus, CNG, or auto-rickshaw to the mosque complex.', 'Part of the \"Mosque City of Bagerhat\". Wear comfortable shoes. A guide can explain the history and architecture. Dress modestly.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(59, 'Nine Dome Mosque (Noi Gombuj Masjid)', 'Historical', 'Located near Khan Jahan Ali\'s Tomb in Bagerhat, this is another beautiful example of Sultanate-era architecture from the 15th century, featuring intricate terracotta designs.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Bagerhat Sadar Upazila, Bagerhat District', 'images/nine_dome_mosque.jpg', 'Built during the time of Khan Jahan Ali. Known for its elegant structure and detailed terracotta ornamentation, particularly on the mihrab.', 'October to March.', 'Often included with the entry to Khan Jahan Ali\'s Tomb complex or may have a small separate fee.', 'Accessible during daylight hours.', 'Admiring the architecture and terracotta work, Photography, Visiting Khan Jahan Ali\'s Tomb and dighi nearby.', 'Department of Archaeology.', 'Located close to Shat Gombuj Mosque and Khan Jahan Ali\'s Tomb in Bagerhat.', 'Usually visited as part of a tour of Bagerhat\'s historical sites. Dress modestly.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(60, 'Dhakeshwari National Temple (Dhakeshwari Mandir)', 'Worship', 'The national Hindu temple of Bangladesh, located in Dhaka. \"Dhakeshwari\" means \"Goddess of Dhaka\". It is a major pilgrimage site for Hindus.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Dhakeshwari Road, Lalbagh, Dhaka', 'images/d.jpg', 'Believed to have been built in the 12th century by Ballal Sen of the Sena dynasty, though the current structure is largely modern due to renovations. It is the most important Hindu place of worship in Bangladesh.', 'Throughout the year. Major festivals like Durga Puja attract huge crowds.', 'No entry fee, but donations are welcome.', 'Open daily, typically from morning to evening (e.g., 8 AM to 1 PM, and 4 PM to 8 PM). Timings may vary, especially during festivals.', 'Offering prayers, Participating in religious rituals and festivals, Admiring temple architecture, Learning about Hindu traditions.', 'Temple committee/authorities.', 'Located in Old Dhaka, accessible by rickshaw, CNG, or auto-rickshaw.', 'Dress modestly. Remove shoes before entering the main temple areas. Be respectful of religious customs and ongoing worship. Photography might be restricted in certain sanctums.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(61, 'Ramna Kali Mandir (Ramna Kali Temple)', 'Worship', 'A historic Hindu temple in Dhaka, dedicated to Goddess Kali. It was destroyed during the 1971 Bangladesh Liberation War and later rebuilt.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Ramna Park Area (near Suhrawardy Udyan), Dhaka', 'images/ramna_kali_mandir.jpg', 'The original temple was centuries old. Its destruction in 1971 was a significant event. The rebuilt temple stands as a symbol of resilience and faith.', 'Throughout the year. Kali Puja is a major festival celebrated here.', 'No entry fee, donations accepted.', 'Open daily, specific puja timings apply. General visiting usually during daylight hours.', 'Offering prayers, Participating in religious ceremonies, Reflecting on its history.', 'Temple committee.', 'Located near Ramna Park and Suhrawardy Udyan in central Dhaka.', 'Dress modestly. Be respectful of religious practices. The temple has a poignant history.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(62, 'Chandranath Temple', 'Worship', 'An ancient Hindu temple dedicated to Lord Shiva, located on the summit of Chandranath Hill in Sitakunda, Chattogram. A major pilgrimage site, especially during Shivratri.', 'Bangladesh', 'Chattogram', 'Sitakunda Upazila, Chattogram District', 'images/chandranath_temple.jpg', 'Believed to be a Shakti Peetha where a part of Goddess Sati\'s body fell. The temple is ancient, though renovated over time. The hill itself has mythological significance.', 'October to March (cooler weather for climbing). Shivratri festival (Feb/Mar) attracts a large number of pilgrims.', 'No entry fee for the temple, but donations are welcome. Fees for parking or local transport to footh', 'Temple is generally open daily. Climbing the hill is best done during daylight hours.', 'Trekking/climbing the hill (approx. 1.5-2 hours), Offering prayers at Chandranath Temple and other smaller shrines on the hill, Enjoying panoramic views from the summit, Participating in Shivratri festival.', 'Temple committee. Local guides available at Sitakunda.', 'From Chattogram city, take a bus to Sitakunda Bazar. From Sitakunda, take a CNG/auto-rickshaw to the foothill of Chandranath Hill. Then, climb the stairs/trail to the top.', 'The climb involves many stairs and can be strenuous. Wear comfortable shoes and carry water. Dress modestly. Be respectful of religious customs. The area can be very crowded during festivals.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(63, 'Jessoreswari Kali Temple', 'Worship', 'A famous Hindu temple dedicated to Goddess Kali, located in Ishwaripur, Satkhira. It is one ofthe 51 Shakti Peethas.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Ishwaripur, Shyamnagar Upazila, Satkhira District', 'images/jessoreswari_temple.jpg', 'According to Hindu mythology, the palm of Sati\'s left hand fell here. The temple was established by Maharaja Pratapaditya or an earlier king. It is a significant pilgrimage site.', 'Throughout the year. Special pujas and festivals attract many devotees.', 'No entry fee, donations welcome.', 'Open daily, specific puja timings. General visits usually during daylight.', 'Offering prayers, Participating in religious rituals, Learning about the Shakti Peetha tradition, Exploring the temple architecture.', 'Temple committee.', 'From Satkhira town, travel to Shyamnagar Upazila. From Shyamnagar, take local transport to Ishwaripur village.', 'Dress modestly. Respect religious customs. The temple holds great religious importance for Hindus. Inquire about any ongoing festivals for a richer experience.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(64, 'Tara Masjid (Star Mosque)', 'Worship', 'A historic mosque in Old Dhaka, famous for its ornate design with mosaics of étoiles (stars). Originally built in the late 18th or early 19th century, later renovated and expanded.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Armanitola, Old Dhaka', 'images/tara_masjid.jpg', 'Built by Mirza Ghulam Pir. The distinctive star-patterned decoration (Chinitikri work) was added during a renovation in the early 20th century by Ali Jan Bepari.', 'Throughout the year. Visit outside prayer times for detailed viewing.', 'No entry fee.', 'Open for daily prayers. For general visits, avoid main prayer congregations.', 'Admiring the unique star-patterned mosaic work, Observing Mughal-influenced architecture, Photography (exterior), Offering prayers (for Muslims).', 'Mosque committee.', 'Located in Armanitola, Old Dhaka. Accessible by rickshaw or CNG from various parts of the city.', 'A beautiful example of architectural decoration. Dress modestly. Maintain silence if visiting during prayer times.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(65, 'Choto Sona Masjid (Small Golden Mosque)', 'Historical', 'A 15th-century Sultanate-era mosque in Gaur (Chapainawabganj district), known for its beautiful stone carving and once-gilded domes (hence the name \"Golden Mosque\").', 'Bangladesh', 'Rajshahi', 'Shibganj Upazila, Chapainawabganj District (near India border)', 'images/choto_sona_mosjid.jpg', 'Built between 1493 and 1519 by Wali Muhammad during the reign of Sultan Alauddin Husain Shah. An exquisite example of Bengal Sultanate architecture.', 'October to March.', 'Entry fee applicable (managed by Dept. of Archaeology, e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals).', 'Typically 9/10 AM to 5 PM (verify locally, may close for lunch or on certain days).', 'Admiring stone carvings and architectural details, Photography, Learning about Sultanate history, Visiting other Gaur ruins nearby (e.g., Darasbari Mosque, Khania Dighi Mosque).', 'Department of Archaeology. Local guides.', 'From Chapainawabganj town, take a bus or CNG to Sona Masjid Land Port area. The mosque is located nearby.', 'Located near the India-Bangladesh border; be mindful of security. Combine with a visit to other Gaur monuments. Dress modestly.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(66, 'Ronvijoypur Mosque (Ronbijoypur Mosque)', 'Historical', 'Located in Bagerhat, this mosque is notable for having the largest single dome in Bangladesh from the Sultanate period. Built in the 15th century.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Bagerhat Sadar Upazila, Bagerhat District', 'images/ronvijoypur_mosque.jpg', 'Attributed to Khan Jahan Ali or his followers. Its massive single dome is an architectural feat of its time.', 'October to March.', 'May be freely accessible or included with a general Bagerhat sites ticket.', 'Accessible during daylight hours.', 'Observing the large dome and mosque architecture, Photography, Visiting as part of Bagerhat historical tour.', 'Department of Archaeology.', 'Located in Bagerhat, usually visited along with Shat Gombuj Mosque and other sites.', 'Part of the UNESCO World Heritage \"Mosque City of Bagerhat\". Dress modestly.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(67, 'Guthia Mosque (Baitul Aman Jame Masjid Complex)', 'Worship', 'A large and visually stunning mosque complex in Barisal, built in recent times (early 21st century). Known for its intricate design, beautiful landscaping, and large scale.', 'Bangladesh', 'Barisal', 'Guthia Union, Wazirpur Upazila, Barisal District', 'images/guthia_mosque.jpg', 'Built by S. Sharfuddin Ahmed Santu, a local businessman and philanthropist, inspired by famous mosques around the world. The complex also includes a madrasa, orphanage, and eidgah.', 'Throughout the year. Evenings with illumination are particularly beautiful.', 'No entry fee. Donations are welcome.', 'Open for daily prayers. Visitors usually allowed throughout the day, outside of main prayer congregations. Check for specific visiting hours if any.', 'Admiring the modern Islamic architecture and intricate calligraphy, Exploring the landscaped gardens and ponds, Photography, Offering prayers (for Muslims).', 'Mosque committee/management.', 'From Barisal city, take a bus, CNG, or auto-rickshaw towards Wazirpur/Guthia (approx. 20 km).', 'A modern architectural marvel. Dress modestly. Maintain silence and respect, especially during prayer times. The complex is quite large and well-maintained.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(68, 'Baitul Mukarram National Mosque', 'Worship', 'The national mosque of Bangladesh, located in the heart of Dhaka. It is one of the largest mosques in South Asia, with a distinctive design resembling the Kaaba in Mecca.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Paltan, Dhaka', 'images/baitul_mukarram_mosque.jpg', 'Completed in 1968. Its design was by architect T Abdul Hussain Thariani. It serves as a major center for Islamic activities and prayers in the country.', 'Throughout the year.', 'No entry fee.', 'Open for all daily prayers. For general visits by non-Muslims, it\'s best to go outside of main prayer times (especially Friday noon prayer) and inquire respectfully at an entrance.', 'Offering prayers (for Muslims), Admiring the unique architecture, Experiencing the scale of the mosque, Visiting the Islamic Foundation library and bookshops in the complex.', 'Mosque management committee, Islamic Foundation Bangladesh.', 'Centrally located in Dhaka, easily accessible by bus, CNG, rickshaw from anywhere in the city.', 'Dress very modestly (cover head, arms, and legs for women; long pants for men). Remove shoes before entering prayer halls. Maintain silence and decorum. Photography might be restricted inside prayer halls. It\'s a very active place of worship.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(69, 'Orokandi Thakur Bari', 'Worship', 'A sacred pilgrimage site for the Matua Mahasangha, a Hindu reformist sect. It is the birthplace of Harichand Thakur, the founder of the Matua faith, and his son Guruchand Thakur.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Orakandi, Kashiani Upazila, Gopalganj District', 'images/orakandi_thakurbari.jpg', 'Established in the 19th century, Orakandi is the main spiritual center for millions of Matua followers in Bangladesh and India. It holds immense religious and cultural significance for the community.', 'Throughout the year. Major festivals like Baruni Snan and the birth/death anniversaries of Harichand and Guruchand Thakur attract vast numbers of devotees.', 'No entry fee. Donations are welcome.', 'The temple complex is generally open daily. Specific timings for rituals and darshan may apply.', 'Offering prayers, Participating in religious congregations and kirtans, Visiting the temples dedicated to Harichand and Guruchand Thakur, Taking a holy dip in Kamona Sagar (pond), Learning about Matua philosophy.', 'Orakandi Thakur Bari Managing Committee.', 'From Gopalganj town or Kashiani Upazila headquarters, take local transport (bus, auto-rickshaw, CNG) to Orakandi village.', 'Dress modestly and respectfully. Remove shoes before entering temple premises. This is a very important religious site; maintain decorum. Inquire about ongoing events or festivals. Basic accommodation and food facilities may be available locally, especially during festivals.', '2025-06-02 06:45:30'),
(70, 'Rupsha River & Rupsha Bridge', 'River', 'The Rupsha River is a major river in southwestern Bangladesh, flowing through Khulna. The Rupsha Bridge (Khan Jahan Ali Bridge) is an iconic landmark over this river, connecting Khulna with Mongla Port.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Khulna City & Batiaghata Upazila, Khulna', 'images/rupsha_bridge.jpg', 'The river is vital for local economy and transportation. The bridge, opened in 2005, significantly improved connectivity.', 'October to March (pleasant weather for riverside activities). Evenings are popular for bridge views.', 'No fee for viewing the river or bridge. Toll applies for vehicles crossing the bridge.', 'River is always accessible. Bridge is open 24/7 for traffic.', 'Enjoying views of the river and bridge (especially at sunset/night when illuminated), Boat rides on Rupsha River, Photography, Visiting riverside parks or restaurants.', 'Local boatmen, Khulna City Corporation for park info.', 'The bridge is a major landmark in Khulna city, easily accessible by road. Riverside areas can be reached by local transport.', 'Evening views of the illuminated bridge are popular. Boat rides offer a different perspective. Be cautious near the riverbank.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(71, 'Horintana Eco Park', 'Forest', 'An eco-park located near Khulna city, offering a green space with some deer, birds, and recreational facilities. A place for locals to connect with nature.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Horintana, Khulna Sadar (near Khulna University)', 'images/horintana_eco_park.jpg', 'Developed to provide a recreational green space and conserve local flora/fauna.', 'October to March (pleasant weather).', 'Small entry fee usually applies (e.g., BDT 10-20).', 'Typically open during daylight hours (e.g., 9 AM to 5 PM).', 'Walking, Picnicking, Viewing deer and birds (limited), Boating (if available), Relaxing in nature.', 'Park management/Forest Department.', 'From Khulna city, take local transport (CNG/auto-rickshaw) towards Khulna University; the park is nearby.', 'A good spot for a short outing from Khulna city. Facilities might be basic. Best to carry own snacks/water if planning a longer stay.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(72, 'Crocodile Breeding Center, Karamjol', 'Forest', 'Located in Karamjol, Sundarbans, this center is dedicated to the breeding and conservation of saltwater crocodiles. It also has a deer breeding center and offers short boardwalk trails into the mangrove.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Karamjol, Mongla Upazila (Sundarbans area)', 'images/karamjol_crocodile_center.jpg', 'An important initiative by the Forest Department for crocodile conservation in the Sundarbans.', 'November to February (best for Sundarbans visits).', 'Entry fee for Karamjol tourist spot (around BDT 20-150, varies for locals/foreigners/students). Boat', 'Typically 8 AM to 5 PM.', 'Observing crocodiles in enclosures, Seeing spotted deer, Walking on boardwalks through mangrove forest, Photography, Learning about Sundarbans ecosystem.', 'Karamjol Forest Office.', 'From Mongla, hire a boat or join a tour to Karamjol. It\'s usually the first stop on a Sundarbans day trip.', 'A good introduction to the Sundarbans. Wear comfortable shoes. Mosquito repellent is advisable. Do not feed the animals.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(73, 'Fultola (Flower Gardens & Nurseries)', 'Other', 'Fultola in Jashore (Jessore) district is renowned for its extensive flower cultivation, particularly marigolds, roses, and gladioli. It\'s a hub for the flower trade in Bangladesh.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Godkhali Union, Jhikargachha Upazila, Jashore (Jessore)', 'images/fultola_godkhali_flowers.jpg', 'Known as the \"Flower Capital of Bangladesh\". The area transformed into a major floriculture hub over the last few decades.', 'December to March (peak blooming season for many flowers, especially for festivals like Pohela Falgun, Valentine\'s Day, Ekushey February).', 'Generally no entry fee to view fields from roadsides. If entering specific nurseries/gardens, permis', 'Fields are accessible visually anytime. Nurseries have their own operating hours.', 'Walking or cycling through vast flower fields, Photography, Purchasing fresh flowers, Learning about floriculture from local farmers.', 'Local flower farmer associations or nursery owners.', 'From Jashore town, take a bus or CNG towards Benapole and get down at Godkhali. From there, explore the flower fields by van or on foot.', 'Best to visit early morning to see fresh blooms and market activities. Be respectful of private property. Ask for permission before entering deep into fields or picking flowers. The vibrant colors are a photographer\'s delight.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(74, 'Shrine of Khan Jahan Ali', 'Historical', 'The mausoleum of Khan Jahan Ali, a 15th-century Muslim saint and ruler who founded the \"Mosque City of Bagerhat\". A revered pilgrimage site with a large dighi (pond) containing tame crocodiles.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Bagerhat Sadar Upazila, Bagerhat District', 'images/khan_jahan_ali_shrine.jpg', 'Khan Jahan Ali (died c. 1459) was a key figure in spreading Islam and establishing settlements in southern Bengal. His tomb is a major pilgrimage site.', 'Throughout the year.', 'No entry fee for the shrine, but donations are welcome. Small fee for feeding crocodiles (if allowed', 'Open daily, from early morning to late evening.', 'Paying respects at the shrine, Observing the architecture, Visiting the dighi and seeing the crocodiles (Kala Pahar, Dhala Pahar), Photography (respectful).', 'Shrine management committee.', 'Located in Bagerhat town, easily accessible by local transport. Usually visited with Shat Gombuj Mosque.', 'Dress modestly. Remove shoes before entering the shrine. Be respectful of religious customs. The crocodiles are considered sacred by some; observe them from a safe distance.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(75, 'Jordar Mosque, Tala', 'Worship', 'A small but architecturally interesting mosque in Tala Upazila, Satkhira, known for its unique design and local historical context. May refer to a specific local mosque of significance.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Tala Upazila, Satkhira District', 'images/jordar_mosque_tala.jpg', 'Local historical mosques often reflect regional architectural styles and the spread of Islam in rural Bengal.', 'Throughout the year.', 'Likely no entry fee.', 'Open for daily prayers.', 'Observing local mosque architecture, Offering prayers (for Muslims), Learning about local history from community members.', 'Local mosque committee.', 'From Satkhira town, travel to Tala Upazila. Inquire locally for the specific \"Jordar Mosque\".', 'As this is a local mosque, ensure respectful attire and behavior. It might be best to visit with someone from the local community or after inquiring about appropriate visiting times.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(76, 'S. M. Sultan Memorial Museum (Shishu Swarga)', 'Historical', 'A museum and art gallery in Narail dedicated to the life and works of Sheikh Mohammed Sultan (S. M. Sultan), one of Bangladesh\'s most renowned painters, known for his depictions of rural life and robust figures.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Masimdia, Narail Sadar Upazila, Narail District', 'images/sm_sultan_museum.jpg', 'Preserves the artworks, personal belongings, and legacy of S. M. Sultan. The complex also includes a children\'s park (Shishu Swarga) and a boat he used.', 'Throughout the year. Cooler months (October-March) are pleasant.', 'Small entry fee usually applicable (e.g., BDT 10-20).', 'Typically open from 10 AM to 5 PM (closed on certain days like Sundays or public holidays - verify locally).', 'Viewing S. M. Sultan\'s paintings and drawings, Exploring his personal artifacts, Visiting the Shishu Swarga, Photography (check rules for inside gallery).', 'Museum authorities, Narail District Administration.', 'From Narail town, take a rickshaw or auto-rickshaw to Masimdia.', 'A must-visit for art lovers and those interested in Bangladeshi culture. The museum provides insights into the artist\'s unique style and philosophy.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(77, 'Joypura Zamindar Palace (Joypur Zamindar Bari)', 'Historical', 'Ruins of an old zamindar palace in Pabna district, reflecting the region\'s feudal past and colonial-era architecture.', 'Bangladesh', 'Rajshahi', 'Joypur (Joypura), Ishwardi Upazila, Pabna District (Location may vary, confirm locally)', 'images/joypura_zamindar_bari.jpg', 'Represents the lifestyle and influence of local landlords (zamindars) during the British colonial period. Many such palaces are now in ruins.', 'October to March (cooler weather for exploring).', 'Generally no entry fee as it\'s often in a state of ruin or open access.', 'Accessible during daylight hours.', 'Exploring the architectural remnants, Photography, Imagining the past glory of the zamindars.', 'Local residents or cultural offices for more specific history.', 'From Pabna or Ishwardi town, inquire about Joypura village and the Zamindar Bari. Local transport (CNG/auto) may be needed.', 'Many zamindar palaces are in a dilapidated state. Be cautious while exploring. Respect any private property if parts are occupied. Good for those interested in historical ruins and colonial architecture.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(78, 'Chanchra Rajbari (Zamindar Palace)', 'Historical', 'A historic zamindar palace in Jashore (Jessore) district, known for its distinctive architecture featuring a mix of local and European styles. Includes temples and other structures within the complex.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Chanchra, Jashore Sadar Upazila, Jashore District', 'images/chanchra_rajbari.webp', 'Seat of the Chanchra Raj family, influential zamindars in the region. The complex showcases the grandeur of the feudal era.', 'October to March.', 'Small entry fee may apply if maintained as a tourist spot. Some parts might be private or in disrepa', 'Typically accessible during daylight hours.', 'Exploring the palace ruins and structures, Visiting the temples (e.g., Shiv Mandir), Photography, Learning about the local zamindari history.', 'Local administration or cultural office.', 'From Jashore town, take local transport (CNG/auto-rickshaw) to Chanchra (approx. 3-4 km).', 'Some buildings might be in a state of decay; exercise caution. Good for history and architecture enthusiasts.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08');
INSERT INTO `tourist_spots` (`spot_id`, `name`, `type`, `description`, `country`, `division`, `location`, `image_url`, `historical_significance`, `best_time_to_visit`, `entry_fee`, `opening_hours`, `things_to_do`, `contact_info`, `how_to_go`, `special_tips`, `created_at`) VALUES
(79, 'Liberation War Memorial Museum, Jashore', 'Historical', 'A museum in Jashore dedicated to preserving and showcasing the history and artifacts of the Bangladesh Liberation War of 1971, with a focus on the events in the Jashore region.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Jashore City', 'images/jashore_liberation_war_museum.jpg', 'Jashore was the first district to be liberated during the 1971 war. The museum holds significant local and national importance in commemorating the war.', 'Throughout the year. Check for specific holidays.', 'Small entry fee may apply.', 'Typically open from 10 AM to 5 PM (closed on specific days like weekends or government holidays - verify locally).', 'Viewing exhibits (photographs, documents, weapons, personal belongings of freedom fighters), Learning about the Liberation War history, Paying respects to martyrs.', 'Museum authorities.', 'Located within Jashore city, accessible by local transport.', 'An important place to learn about Bangladesh\'s struggle for independence. Photography rules might apply inside.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(80, 'Mujibnagar Memorial Complex (First Provisional Govt. Memorial)', 'Historical', 'Located in Meherpur district, this complex commemorates the place where the first provisional government of Bangladesh was formed and took oath on April 17, 1971, during the Liberation War. Includes a large memorial, museum, and map of sectors.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Baidyanathtala, Mujibnagar Upazila, Meherpur District', 'images/mujibnagar_memorial.jpg', 'A site of immense national importance, marking the formal establishment of the Government of Bangladesh during the war of independence.', 'Throughout the year. National holidays like Independence Day (Mar 26) and Victory Day (Dec 16) see special observances.', 'Entry fee for the museum and complex (e.g., BDT 20-50).', 'Typically open from 9 AM to 5 PM (verify timings, especially on holidays).', 'Visiting the main memorial sculpture, Exploring the museum depicting events of the Liberation War, Viewing the large map illustrating the 11 sectors of the war, Reflecting on the history of Bangladesh\'s independence.', 'Mujibnagar Complex authorities, District Administration Meherpur.', 'From Meherpur town or Kushtia/Jhenaidah, take a bus or CNG to Mujibnagar (Baidyanathtala).', 'A very significant historical site. Allow ample time to explore the complex and museum. Guides may be available. Wear respectful attire.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(81, 'Alamdanga Liberation War Memorial', 'Historical', 'A memorial in Alamdanga, Chuadanga, dedicated to the martyrs and events of the Bangladesh Liberation War of 1971 in that region.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Alamdanga Upazila, Chuadanga District', 'images/alamdanga_liberation_memorial.webp', 'Commemorates local contributions and sacrifices during the 1971 war.', 'Throughout the year.', 'Likely no entry fee, as it\'s an open memorial.', 'Accessible anytime, but best visited during daylight.', 'Paying respects to martyrs, Reflecting on the Liberation War history, Photography.', 'Local Upazila administration or Muktijoddha Sangsad.', 'Located in Alamdanga town, accessible by local transport from Chuadanga district headquarters.', 'Local memorials like this are important for understanding regional history of the Liberation War.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(82, 'Lalon Shah Mazar (Shrine of Baul Saint Lalon Fakir)', '', 'The shrine and akhra (commune) of Lalon Shah, one of the most revered Baul saints, philosophers, and songwriters of Bengal. Located in Kushtia.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Cheuria, Kumarkhali Upazila, Kushtia District', 'images/lalon_shah_mazar.jpg', 'Lalon (c. 1774–1890) was a mystic, songwriter, and social reformer whose songs espouse humanism and critique religious dogma. His shrine is a major pilgrimage site for Bauls and admirers.', 'Throughout the year. Lalon Smaran Utshab (festivals commemorating his birth and death anniversaries) attract huge crowds and Baul singers.', 'No entry fee for the shrine complex. Donations are welcome. Fees may apply for specific events or mu', 'Open daily. The atmosphere is vibrant during festivals.', 'Paying respects at the shrine, Listening to Baul music (especially during festivals or evenings), Visiting the Lalon Museum (if established/open), Interacting with Baul devotees, Experiencing the unique spiritual and cultural ambiance.', 'Lalon Academy, Kushtia. Shrine committee.', 'From Kushtia town, take a rickshaw, auto-rickshaw, or CNG to Cheuria (approx. 2 km).', 'A very important cultural and spiritual site. Dress modestly. Be respectful of Baul traditions and devotees. Photography is generally allowed but be discreet. The Lalon festivals are a unique cultural experience.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(83, 'Shelaidaha Kuthibari (Rabindranath Tagore\'s House)', 'Historical', 'A country house where Nobel laureate Rabindranath Tagore lived for a period and composed many of his famous literary works. Now a museum.', 'Bangladesh', 'Khulna', 'Shelaidaha, Kumarkhali Upazila, Kushtia District', 'images/shelaidaha_kuthibari.jpg', 'Tagore managed his family\'s zamindari estates from here in the late 19th and early 20th centuries. The serene environment by the Padma River inspired much of his poetry and songs.', 'October to March (pleasant weather).', 'Entry fee applicable (e.g., BDT 20-100 for locals, higher for foreigners).', 'Typically 10 AM to 5 PM (closed Sundays and public holidays, half-day Mondays - verify locally).', 'Exploring the rooms and exhibits showcasing Tagore\'s life and belongings, Walking in the gardens, Enjoying views of the Padma River (though the river has shifted course), Photography, Reflecting on Tagore\'s literary contributions.', 'Kuthibari Museum authorities, Department of Archaeology.', 'From Kushtia town, take a bus or CNG/auto-rickshaw to Shelaidaha (approx. 15 km).', 'A must-visit for admirers of Rabindranath Tagore. Check museum opening hours. Combine with a visit to Lalon Shah Mazar if in Kushtia.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(84, 'Hardinge Bridge', 'Historical', 'An iconic steel railway bridge over the Padma River, connecting Pabna and Kushtia districts. A marvel of British engineering, opened in 1915.', 'Bangladesh', 'Rajshahi', 'Paksey, Ishwardi Upazila, Pabna (connects to Bheramara, Kushtia)', 'images/hardinge_bridge.jpg', 'Named after Lord Hardinge, then Viceroy of India. It played a crucial role in railway communication in Bengal and is still a vital link.', 'Throughout the year. Evenings offer good views with illumination (if active).', 'No fee to view the bridge. Train fare if traveling over it.', 'Bridge is operational for trains. Viewing points accessible anytime.', 'Viewing the impressive steel structure, Photography, Watching trains pass, Enjoying views of the Padma River, Visiting nearby Lalon Shah Bridge (road bridge).', 'Bangladesh Railway.', 'Accessible from Paksey (Pabna side) or Bheramara (Kushtia side). Both have railway stations. Viewing points are available near the bridge.', 'A significant engineering landmark. Do not walk on the railway tracks. Be cautious near the riverbanks. The Lalon Shah road bridge runs parallel and offers good views of Hardinge Bridge.', '2025-06-02 07:38:08'),
(85, 'Monpura Island', 'Sea', 'An offshore island in the Bay of Bengal under Bhola district, known for its natural beauty, mangrove forests, deer, and serene beaches. It\'s a relatively less crowded destination.', 'Bangladesh', 'Barisal', 'Monpura Upazila, Bhola District', 'images/monpura_island.jpg', 'Historically an isolated island, it has a unique local culture and is gradually gaining attention for eco-tourism.', 'November to February (pleasant weather and calmer seas for travel).', 'No specific entry fee for the island. Launch/boat fares apply.', 'Accessible by launch/boat, typically day and night services available from major points like Dhaka or Bhola.', 'Exploring beaches, Visiting mangrove areas, Spotting deer (Monpura Deer Sanctuary), Bird watching, Experiencing local island life and fishing communities, Cycling, Photography.', 'Local Upazila administration, Forest Department for sanctuary information.', 'From Dhaka (Sadarghat) or Barisal/Bhola, take a launch directly to Monpura. The journey can be long (8-12+ hours from Dhaka).', 'Remote island with basic tourist facilities. Book accommodation (if any) or arrange homestays in advance. Carry essentials like power bank, first-aid, insect repellent. Respect local culture and environment. Ideal for those seeking an offbeat and nature-centric experience.', '2025-06-02 07:51:30'),
(86, 'Taltoli Sea Beach (Shuvo Shondha)', 'Sea', 'A relatively new and less commercialized sea beach in Barguna district, known for its tranquility, Jhau bon (pine forest), and scenic beauty. Often referred to as \"Shuvo Shondha\" (Auspicious Evening) beach.', 'Bangladesh', 'Barisal', 'Taltali Upazila, Barguna District', 'images/taltoli_beach.jpg', 'Gaining popularity as an alternative to more crowded beaches, offering a peaceful coastal experience.', 'October to March (pleasant weather).', 'Generally free to access.', 'Accessible during daylight hours.', 'Relaxing on the quiet beach, Walking through the Jhau bon, Photography, Enjoying sunsets, Picnicking, Experiencing local coastal life.', 'Local Upazila Parishad, Barguna.', 'From Barguna district town, take local transport (bus, CNG, motorcycle) to Taltali Upazila, then towards the beach area. Road conditions may vary.', 'Facilities are likely to be basic as it\'s a developing tourist spot. Carry own food, water, and essentials. Good for a day trip or for those seeking solitude. Maintain cleanliness.', '2025-06-02 07:51:30'),
(87, 'Nishanbaria Sea Beach', 'Sea', 'A lesser-known sea beach in Barguna district, offering a natural and rustic coastal environment. It is part of the wider coastal belt of Patuakhali-Barguna.', 'Bangladesh', 'Barisal', 'Taltali Upazila (or near Patharghata), Barguna District', 'images/nishanbaria_beach.jpg', 'Represents the natural coastal landscape of southern Bangladesh.', 'October to March (pleasant weather).', 'Generally free.', 'Accessible during daylight hours.', 'Beach walking, Exploring local fishing activities, Photography, Enjoying the natural scenery.', 'Local Union Parishad or Upazila office for specific information.', 'From Barguna or Patharghata, inquire locally for directions and transport options (likely local buses, motorcycles, or trawlers if near estuaries).', 'This is likely a very offbeat location with minimal tourist infrastructure. Ideal for adventurous travelers. Verify current accessibility and local conditions before planning a visit. Carry all necessary supplies.', '2025-06-02 07:51:30'),
(88, 'National Parliament House (Jatiya Sangsad Bhaban)', 'Historical', 'The house of the Parliament of Bangladesh, located in Sher-e-Bangla Nagar in Dhaka. It is one of the largest legislative complexes in the world and an architectural masterpiece designed by Louis Kahn.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Sher-e-Bangla Nagar, Dhaka', 'images/jatiya_sangsad_bhaban.jpg', 'Designed by renowned architect Louis I. Kahn, construction started in 1961 and was completed in 1982. It stands as a symbol of democracy and modern architecture in Bangladesh.', 'Throughout the year. Exterior viewing is always possible. Interior tours usually require prior permission.', 'No entry fee for viewing from outside. Interior tours are restricted and require special permission.', 'Exterior accessible anytime. For interior visits, contact Parliament Secretariat for procedures and timings (usually for organized groups, students, or with special clearance).', 'Admiring the iconic modernist architecture, Photography (exterior), Learning about its design and history, Visiting the surrounding gardens and Crescent Lake (Chandrima Udyan).', 'Bangladesh Parliament Secretariat (for tour inquiries).', 'Located in a central area of Dhaka (Sher-e-Bangla Nagar), accessible by car, CNG, or bus.', 'Interior access is highly restricted for security reasons. The exterior and surrounding areas (like Chandrima Udyan) are popular for walks and photography. Respect the high-security zone.', '2025-06-02 07:58:21'),
(89, 'Hatirjheel Lake', 'River', 'A large lakefront and transportation system in Dhaka, connecting various parts of the city. It has been developed with bridges, viaducts, walkways, and recreational facilities.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Hatirjheel (connecting Tejgaon, Gulshan, Badda, Banasree, Rampura, Moghbazar), Dhaka', 'images/hatirjheel_lake.jpg', 'Originally a stagnant water body (jheel), it was transformed into a major integrated project to improve Dhaka\'s traffic, drainage, and environment, officially opened in 2013.', 'Throughout the year. Evenings are particularly popular for its lighting and ambiance.', 'Generally free to access walkways, bridges, and public areas. Fees apply for water taxi services and', 'Open 24/7. Water taxis and specific recreational facilities have operating hours.', 'Walking or jogging on walkways, Enjoying boat rides (water taxi), Cycling, Photography (especially of bridges and night illumination), Relaxing by the lakeside, Visiting cafes and restaurants.', 'RAJUK (Rajdhani Unnayan Kartripakkha) - project authority. Water taxi operators.', 'Accessible from multiple points in Dhaka including Rampura, Badda Link Road, Gulshan 1, Moghbazar, Tejgaon.', 'Popular spot for locals, can be crowded in evenings and weekends. Water taxis are a convenient way to travel between certain areas. Night views with colorful bridge lights are a key attraction.', '2025-06-02 07:58:21'),
(90, 'Liberation War Museum (Muktijuddho Jadughar)', 'Historical', 'A museum in Agargaon, Dhaka, dedicated to preserving and displaying the history of the Bangladesh Liberation War in 1971, which led to the independence of Bangladesh.', 'Bangladesh', 'Dhaka', 'Agargaon, Dhaka', 'images/liberation_war_museum_dhaka.jpg', 'Established in 1996, it moved to its new, larger premises in Agargaon in 2017. It houses a vast collection of artifacts, documents, photographs, and personal belongings related to the war.', 'Throughout the year. Avoid national holidays if you prefer fewer crowds.', 'Entry fee applicable (e.g., BDT 20-50 for locals, check for student/foreigner rates).', 'Typically open from 10 AM to 5 PM or 6 PM. Closed on Sundays. (Verify current timings from their official website or by calling).', 'Viewing galleries depicting the history leading up to the war, the events of 1971, and the aftermath. Examining artifacts, photographs, and documents. Watching documentaries. Paying tribute to the martyrs.', 'Liberation War Museum authorities. Official website usually has contact details and timings.', 'Located in Agargaon, Dhaka. Accessible by bus, CNG, car, or ride-sharing services.', 'A very important and moving museum. Allow at least 2-3 hours for a thorough visit. Photography rules may apply inside galleries. It\'s an educational experience for all ages.', '2025-06-02 07:58:21');
